title: grandma cline's potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, eggs, celery seed and salt and pepper; set aside.
Mix Miracle Whip, mustard, sugar, vinegar and cream.
Pour over potatoes, onions, etc.
Chill cauliflower and broccoli, then cook and drain.
Mix eggs, salad dressing, cream of mushroom soup, stuffing mix and small onion.
Melt margarine and pour in casserole.
Add broccoli and cauliflower.
Pour over other ingredients.
Add grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snowflake biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and warm water; let set 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk to yeast mixture and set aside.

title: broiled smoked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops (about 24 ounces) on rack in roasting pan. Combine other ingredients.
Brush pork chops with mustard mixture. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp a la scag
directions: Plunge the tomatoes in boiling water until the skins crack, then peel the skins off.
Crush the tomatoes by hand.
In a large skillet or heavy bottom pan, heat the olive oil and slowly fry the onion, garlic and basil.
Add the white wine and reduce by half. Add the crushed tomatoes and cook slowly for 5 to 10 minutes. Place the heavy cream in a large pan and boil until it is reduced to sauce consistency.
Cook shrimp in the tomato sauce and season with salt and pepper.
Stir in the cream, toss the sauce with the spinach linguine and grated cheese.
Sprinkle with fresh parsley and serve immediately.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cinnamon-apple salads
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook and stir cinnamon candies in water until dissolved.
Add apples and cook slowly uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender, turning once during cooking.
Chill apples in syrup several hours, turning once.
Blend cream cheese, milk and lemon juice until smooth; stir in pineapple, dates and walnuts.
Drain apples.
Stuff center of each apple with some cream cheese mixture.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix
all together.
Beat well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle
cup sugar evenly over top and let stand until sugar
dissolves
for
glaze.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Makes 2 pies.

title: egg casserole(for brunch)
directions: Scramble eggs lightly with milk and salt; add cheese.
Put into greased oblong dish and refrigerate overnight. Next morning, mix together soup, mushrooms and sherry.
Pour over eggs; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Great to serve for Christmas morning brunch.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix beaten eggs and oil; add to dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Do not beat.
Fold and blend gently.
Bake in three layers for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: In a small saucepan, cook poppy seed with honey and water for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add cooled poppy seed mixture.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to fruit mixture, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks and fold into batter.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 3 minutes. Remove to rack.
Frost, if desired.

title: lasagne
directions: Remove skins from sausages and brown meat together.
Add onion and pepper and cook until done.
Drain meat, then combine with tomatoes, tomato sauce, spices and molasses.
Cook several hours, until very thick.
Add wine.
Keep warm.

title: frozen strawberry daiquiri
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix.
Add ice until mixture becomes frozen.
Makes 4 drinks.
Garnish with a strawberry or whipped cream, if desired.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: In serving dish,
spread beans on bottom, then avocados mixed with lemon	juice
and
garlic salt.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with taco
seasoning.
Spread
on
top of avocados. Layer on top
of
this
the onion, peppers, olives and cheese. Garnish with tomatoes, diced.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Heat chocolate and water in 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring constantly, 4 minutes.
Stir in milk; cover and heat through, but do not boil.
Just before serving, beat with hand beater until foamy.

title: mushroom strudel
directions: (Hint:
Dill really gives this dish flavor.)

title: anita's ranch chicken
directions: Dilute 1/2 cup Ranch dressing with milk.
Dip chicken in diluted dressing, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place on foil-lined pan and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.
To serve, use Ranch dressing as a sauce for dipping the chicken.

title: scallops with spinach
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons of the olive oil and garlic in a large saute pan on medium heat until it starts to sizzle and garlic begins to brown, about 4 minutes. Add red pepper flakes, handful of spinach and lemon juice; cook, tossing for 1 minute, until spinach is slightly wilted. Continue adding and tossing remaining spinach until wilted, about 3 to 5 minutes. Season with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper. Arrange spinach in center of 4 small plates. Wipe the pan clean and heat 1 tablespoon of the remaining olive oil over high heat until it starts to sizzle. Season scallops with 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper. When the pan is smoking, add scallops and cook for 1 minute on each side. Remove scallops from pan and arrange around spinach on each plate. Put pan back on high heat; add remaining olive oil and the shallots. Saute for no more than 30 seconds. Add white wine, parsley and remaining salt. Cook over high heat until reduced in half, about 1 to 2 minutes, until it has a syrupy consistency. Spoon over scallops and spinach. Serve.

title: creamy goulash
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions on package.
Brown meat in skillet, drain off fat.
Combine all 3 in big bowl and serve.

title: chiffon chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake pans.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Continue beating until very stiff and glossy.
In another bowl, sift remaining sugar, flour, soda and salt; add Wesson oil and half of buttermilk.
Beat 1 minute; add remaining butter, egg yolk and chocolate.
Beat 1 more minute.
Fold in meringue.
Pour in pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: southern fried okra
directions: Cut off stem ends of okra and discard.
Slice okra pods in 1/2-inch slices.
Put meal and flour in Ziploc bag.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat cooking oil in skillet until one piece dropped into oil sizzles immediately.
Put sliced okra pieces in bag with meal/flour mixture and shake well.
Drop pieces into hot greased.
Turn as pieces brown.
Cook crisp.
Drain on paper towels.

title: squash squares
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add salt, pepper, onions, parsley, oil, garlic and cheese.
Add squash and Bisquick.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and vanilla in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil 1 minute (no more).
Add 1 stick margarine, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Spoon out on wax paper; let cool.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover bottom with oil. Add remaining ingredients to pan (chips last).
Stir with a fork or spoon.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: meat balls
directions: Shape in balls and brown in fat slowly. Add
the tomato soup and 1/2 cup water. Cover and cook slowly until meat is well done and sauce is thick.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in margarine. Add milk until it makes soft dough. Flour board and roll out dough; cut out biscuits. Bake at 475° for about 20 minutes.

title: linda's harvard beets
directions: Heat sugar, juice and vinegar in saucepan.
Combine water and cornstarch.
Add gradually to hot liquid to thicken.
Add beets. Stir in butter and salt.
Serve warm.

title: lynn's goulash
directions: Cook macaroni in large pan.
Brown meat with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
When browned, stir in chili powder and flour.
Mix well.
Pour in milk slowly.
Drain macaroni.
Add tomato sauce. Pour meat mixture into macaroni.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: herb tomato and chicken romanesque
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Drain fat. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stir in rice and chicken broth. Arrange pepper and onion on top.
Pour herb sauce over all. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese just before serving.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in Bundt pan.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: sour cream waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Whip egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add melted butter. Follow with sour cream and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients all at once and mix until batter is smooth. Fold in egg whites gently. Bake on heart shaped waffle iron heated until a drop of water sputters.
Serve with whipped cream and jam.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Beat ingredients, except wafers and pie filling, until fluffy. Put wafer in bottom of a foil cupcake liner and fill with mixture to about 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
After baking, put cherry pie filling on top and chill for about 1 hour.

title: cabbage skillet dinner
directions: Put oil in skillet, warm.
Add all ingredients and fry until brown.

title: mulled cider(microwave)
directions: Combine an equal amount of apple juice, whole cloves and cinnamon sticks in 2 mugs or cups.
Heat for 3 1/2 minutes.
Do not allow apple juice to boil.
Garnish with a dollop of whipped cream in each cup and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Complete in one
pan.
Place
pork
chops in baking pan plus also all other vegetables
and tomatoes on top.
Pour oil over just to coat the top only.	Bake at 375° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Please stir at intervals.
Good served with applesauce and good bread.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together.
Choose flavor of Kool-Aid according to decor of party.
Put in freezer and let become icy before serving.
(I have frozen this weeks before taking it out in time to become slushy before serving.)
This recipe is a little over a gallon, serving 16 to 18 cups.
Fruits may be added; frozen strawberries is great with red punch.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with the milk.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased pan.
Turn out on damp cloth, spread with jelly and roll. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: easy spaghetti bake
directions: In skillet that has lid, fry bacon 2 minutes.
Stir in onions and garlic; cook until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Stir in seasonings, tomato sauce and water.
Cover; simmer about 25 minutes.
Stir in ripe olives.
Break half of spaghetti into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half the sauce, then top with half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer until browned and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter and saute onions.
Add flour and stir until combined.
Add milk gradually, then add broccoli.
Cook on low for one hour.
If too thick after sitting, add additional milk.

title: wassail tea
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Add tea bags and steep for 15 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Add other ingredients and cook over low heat until boiling.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve topped with whipped cream (sweetened).

title: vivian's squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash; mash.
Melt margarine.
Put in squash and other in crumbs; line baking dish with 1/2 crumbs.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over crumbs.
Put rest of crumbs on top of squash.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana slush
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except lemon-lime soda, in blender container.
Cover container.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into freezer trays or ice cube trays.
Freeze in freezer until firm.
Place scoops or cubes of frozen slush in a glass.
Fill with lemon-lime soda.

title: marvin wilson's mother's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°; then 30 minutes at 300°.

title: fluffy pink stuff
directions: Thaw strawberries and drain juice into small saucepan. Heat juice until hot (there is not very much juice); do not bring it to a boil. Add Jell-O to juice and stir until sugar is dissolved. Immediately pour hot Jell-O/juice mixture over cream cheese and blend until smooth. Add containers of Cool Whip and continue blending until mixed. STIR in strawberries and marshmallows (do not use mixer for the strawberries or marshmallows, it pulverizes them!). Refrigerate until firm. Makes enough for any potluck or holiday dinner!

title: crock-pot cabbage and ribs
directions: In a crock-pot, layer cabbage, then put in sauerkraut on top of cabbage.
Last, add 5 or 6 ribs and cook on low heat for 8 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix and press crackers and 1 stick melted butter in 10-inch pie plate.
Slice and cook onions in 1 stick butter.
Put over crust.
Mix well the milk, eggs, salt and pepper and pour over onions.
Top with sliced American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until cheese is melted and golden brown.

title: baked ham in champagne
directions: Score ham and place on rack in baking pan.
Cover top with 1 cup brown sugar and pour over 1 bottle champagne.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Combine remaining champagne, brown sugar, honey, ginger and mustard and bring to rolling boil in saucepan.
Lower heat and simmer while basting ham every 15 minutes until done. Garnish with pineapple slices and sliced apples, if desired.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and shredded Cheddar cheese. Add pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, cayenne pepper and salt.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning.
Place on platter.
Layer other ingredients.
Serve cold.
Dip with Fritos or nachos.

title: herbed potato wedges
directions: In bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Brush cut sides of wedges with oil, then dip in seasoning.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: new potatoes dish
directions: Wash and cube potatoes with skins on.
Cook in boiling water until just barely tender.
Remove from heat and drain.
In a 2-quart casserole place a layer of potatoes, half of the bacon, half of the cheese and half of the butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Heat in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Remove from oven and garnish with parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt into 10 x 7 x 8-inch baking pan.
With finger, make 3 holes.
In first hole, pour in butter; in 2nd hole, pour in vinegar; in third hole, pour in vanilla.
Pour water over all.
Mix with fork until blended. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
After baking, pour chips over top and bake 2 to 3 more minutes until melted.
Spread.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa into medium glass bowl.
Add milk and margarine.
Cut margarine in 4 or 5 pieces; arrange around edges, not in center.
Do not stir!
Microwave for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Add vanilla and pecans; stir to blend well.
Pour and spread into an 8-inch pan.

title: feather-light pancakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except egg whites and berries. In a separate bowl, whip egg whites until peaks stand.
Fold eggs into mixture and add berries.
Spray skillet with Pam.
Pour batter by 1/4 cup into skillet.
Cook on both sides until golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: coconut balls
directions: Combine potatoes, powdered sugar, flavoring and coconut.
Form into balls; freeze or chill.
Dip into mixture of melted chocolate chips and paraffin.
Place on wax paper.

title: dilly clam dip
directions: Drain clams; reserve 3 tablespoons liquid and set aside. Place reserved clam liquid, dill and next 5 ingredients in food processor.
Cover; process until smooth.
Spoon mixture into bowl; stir in clams.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: bacon broccoli salad
directions: Mix 2 c. salad dressing, sugar to taste (about 1/2 c.) and 4 Tbsp. vinegar. Pour over ingredients.

title: early bird asparagus supreme
directions: Cook asparagus and drain well.
Arrange cooked asparagus in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter.
Add soup mix, stirring well.
Drizzle mixture over asparagus.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 4-h hot diggety dogs
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients on medium heat until hot dogs are browned on both sides and onion is tender, then add remaining ingredients.
Bring to slight boil and serve.
Great with garlic bread.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: harvard onions
directions: Place onions and water in saucepan. Cover and cook over medium heat until tender, about 12 minutes. In another saucepan, combine sugar, flour, salt and vinegar. Stir until smooth. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir 2 minutes. Stir in butter until melted. Drain onions and add to sauce. Sprinkle with parsley. Yields 5 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well.
Add topping to potato mixture in casserole dish.

title: gert's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the eggs, sugar, Crisco and flavorings together.
Add flour and milk; mix well.
Lightly flour and grease cake pan.
Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until toothpick comes out of center clean.

title: pork chop and sweet potato skillet
directions: Brown chops on both sides in fat in skillet.
Season with salt, pepper and herbs.
Top with onion, potatoes and green pepper; add tomatoes.
Cover and cook slowly 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: barbecued beef stew
directions: Brown beef in oil with garlic.
Chop onions and add to the beef.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over beef.
Cover tightly and simmer about 1 1/2 hours or until the meat is tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in shortening.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Remove onions and mushrooms from skillet.
Brown round steak slowly and thoroughly.
Add flour and mix well.
Add 1 can canned tomatoes, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook very slowly for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add sour cream, onions and mushrooms.
Cover and cook 1/2 hour longer. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sweet crisp pickles
directions: Soak pickles overnight.
Then boil 40 minutes.
Slice cucumbers 1/4-inch thick; cover slices with a solution of 2 cups slaked lime in 2 gallons of water.
Soak 24 hours.
Slaked lime is available from your lumber dealer.
Next day, rinse pickles well and cover with fresh water.
Soak 3 hours longer.
Drain and cover with this mixture.
Soak in a crock container (only).
Pack in jars and seal.

title: lemon marinated asparagus
directions: Whisk together lemon juice and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl; add artichoke quarters and diced pimiento, and gently toss. Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight.
Snap off tough ends of asparagus; cook in boiling salted water to cover 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain asparagus and plunge into ice water to stop cooking process.
Place cooked asparagus in a large heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag, and store overnight in refrigerator, if desired.
Add asparagus to artichoke mixture, and gently toss.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Garnish, if desired.

title: party punch
directions: Add 1 liter bottle lemon-lime drink just before serving.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and chill.

title: no-roll sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar, powdered sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs and mix well. Stir in flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Blend well. Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake for 5 to 8 minutes, until set, but not brown.
Yields 9 to 10 dozen cookies.

title: spinach salad with sweet sour dressing
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly, and pat dry.
Tear into bite-size pieces.
Combine spinach, bean sprouts and next 3 ingredients; toss salad gently.
Chill.
Combine sugar and remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Chill.
Shake dressing well before pouring over salad; toss salad gently.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: deviled egg mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatine on water to soften.
Place over low heat to dissolve.
Cool.
Add salt, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Fold into remaining ingredients. This fills a 3-cup mold.
I double recipe.
Enjoy.

title: herbed chicken quarters
directions: Gently squeeze juice from lemons into large resealable bag. Leave lemon wedges in bag.
Add oil, garlic, basil, thyme, salt and cayenne pepper.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Seal bag and refrigerate 24 hours, turning frequently.
Drain and discard marinade.
Grill chicken over medium heat until juices run clear, turning every 15 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add cocoa, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Alternately add flour and coconut (1/2 cup at a time).
Add nuts and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with marshmallow cream while still warm.
Spread with frosting when completely cooled.

title: no peekee stew
directions: Mix all the ingredients; place in casserole.
Cover and bake 3 hours at 350°.
Do not peek.
May be served over rice or noodles.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cut the onion up in pieces.
Keep broth from chicken.
Take about 1/2 loaf or little more bread, toasted, then take broken up bread and chicken and mix.
Add broth, enough to make it good and moist.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in baking dish.
Bake about 40 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: mexican skillet supper
directions: In 10-inch skillet, combine salad dressing, chicken, broth, rice, chilies, chili powder and cumin.
Mix well.
Add chicken and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and olives.
Cover and continue cooking 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with cheese and let stand 5 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Soften margarine and mix with sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Add pineapple and bread.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and onions; cook until almost done.
Drain and add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cook large cake for 4 hours and 20 minutes at 200°.
Increase heat to brown cake.
In mixing bowl, mix the butter, margarine and sugar; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, until all are added.
Add orange juice with sugar.
Add the flavoring and flour; beat until all is mixed well.
Mix all other ingredients in large pan with flour; coat well before adding to batter.
After adding all ingredients, mix well for about 5 minutes.

title: hamburger balls
directions: Mix together well and roll into balls. Place in two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Preheat oven to 420°.
Set aside until sauce is ready.

title: rice souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine rice, egg yolks, milk, butter and cheese in a bowl.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites with salt in mixer bowl until stiff peaks form.
Fold gently into rice mixture. Spoon into greased 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes or until set and brown.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti for 10 minutes; drain.
Combine with other ingredients and 1 1/2 cups of spaghetti sauce.
In a 3-quart casserole, layer 1/2 cup sauce over bottom, ziti mixture over sauce and top with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Cover and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper. Spread evenly in a 9 or 10-inch quiche or pie plate. Spread pizza sauce. Sprinkle with green onion, green pepper and pepperoni. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or heated throughout. Take out and add Mozzarella cheese; return to oven and bake 5 more minutes or longer if cheese is not melted. Best served with Italian bread.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip. Alternate layers of wafers, bananas and pudding, ending with pudding.
Chill.

title: italian tomato sauce(great sauce with a slightly sweet flavor)
directions: Saute in a large kettle the oil, red onion, garlic, green pepper, basil, bay leaves, salt and oregano.
When onions become clear and soft, add the following ingredients: tomato puree, tomato paste, red wine, chopped tomatoes, sugar and black pepper.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Beat concentrate in large bowl with electric mixer on low speed, about 30 seconds.
Gradually spoon in ice cream; beat until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Freeze until mixture will mound, if necessary.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes or until pie can be cut easily.
Garnish with Citrus Twists and mint leaves.
Store leftover pie in freezer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: south texas bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with chips.

title: golden shark nuggets
directions: Cut shark into chunks (1-inch to 2-inch).
Pour flour into bowl.
Make a well and add egg yolk, beer and salt.
Mix.
Combine milk and water, add half to batter, stir.
Add remaining milk and water mixture, gradually, stirring until batter is smooth.
Let batter rest 30 minutes.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Slice the potatoes on large heavy tin-foil sprayed with Pam. All of the other ingredients are optional and to each persons preference.
Slice margarine and put over all ingredients.
Cover with another piece of heavy tin-foil.
Fold all edges, so completely sealed.
Barbecue for 6 minutes, flip over for 6 more minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop all vegetables coarsely. Pour 1 cup salt over vegetables. Store in refrigerator overnight; drain. Mix the sugar, water, etc., thoroughly and pour over drained vegetables. Cook for 15 minutes; can in hot jars.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger with chili powder and salt and pepper.
Then heat tortillas in microwave (1 to 3 at a time) for 20 to 30 seconds.
Put meat mixture in tortilla and roll (like a burrito). Place in a 13 x 2 x 9-inch pan (or smaller).
Then pour enchilada sauce over.
Add chili (you need to add water to the chili before pouring it over, about 1/2 to 3/4 can of water).
Spread it over the enchiladas.
Bake at 350° (cover with foil) for 45 minutes. Take out and add cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted. Serve with chips and picante.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix Velveeta and Cheddar until soft.
Add and mix cream cheese.
Add Worcestershire, Tabasco and garlic salt.
Make into ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: fresh apple-nut cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add water and cook about 1 minute.
Beat and spread on cake.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to box directions.
Reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Squeeze spinach very thoroughly.
Melt butter; add flour. Stir in spinach liquid and evaporated milk.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add seasonings and cheese.
Stir until the cheese is melted and mix with the spinach.
Spoon into a shallow greased casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and drizzle with a little melted butter or oil.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes until bubbling.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix together drained corn, peas and green beans.
Add onion, pepper, celery and mushrooms.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cool completely.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend together sugar, brown sugar, margarine, shortening, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: In medium saucepan, bring water, milk and margarine to the boiling point. Stir in noodles and Alfredo sauce and broccoli. Continue boiling over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 8 minutes or until noodles are tender. Stir in chicken; heat through.
Makes about 2 servings.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add and beat 2 minutes the oil, 1/3 cup buttermilk and bananas.
Add and beat 2 more minutes the 1/3 cup buttermilk and unbeaten eggs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a loaf pan.
Bake 30 minutes for layers.
Two-thirds cup of nuts may be added.

title: apple layer cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; toss to mix.
Let stand 30 minutes. Add flour, salt and soda.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed. Divide batter.
Pour into three 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Frost cake with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar, salt, dill weed and garlic powder.
Toss with vegetables.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in thin strips.
Trim off fat.
Brown meat in skillet with mushrooms in butter.
Add onions.
Combine soup, tomato paste and seasoning; add to meat mixture (cover).
Simmer for 1 hour. When you go to serve, stir in sour cream.
Serve with fluffy hot rice.

title: creme caramel
directions: Place melted caramel into bottom of Bundt-shaped pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour on top of caramel.
Bake at 250° for about 1 hour.
When mixture is dry, remove from oven. Let cool, then remove from pan by turning pan upside down.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend flour, chicken bouillon, salt, sage and pepper.
Add milk and water.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Heat until bubbly.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
In large mixing bowl, add soup to chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients well and pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole sprayed with Pam.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Put half of cracker mixture into a baking dish.
Add the cooked broccoli and the cubed Velveeta.
Top with rest of cracker mixture.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash and sort beans. Add 2 quarts hot water. Cover and soak overnight.
Drain well. Discard the liquid and add cold water to cover the beans to about 1/2-inch over top.
Add onions, peppers, celery, ham, salt, cayenne and black pepper to beans. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add onion tops and parsley to beans. Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
Serve 1/2 cup beans over 1/2 cup rice.
Contains 244 calories, 43 gm. cholesterol, 14 mg. protein, 3 gm. fat and 381 mg. sodium per serving.

title: chocolate surprise cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan.
In a small mixing bowl use electric mixer and beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until blended and set aside.
Prepare cake as label directs; fold in chocolate morsels.
Pour chocolate batter into prepared pan; evenly cover with cream cheese mixture.
Bake until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean, 44 to 55 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: the chicken dish
directions: Saute chicken in butter until cooked through.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Save the pan juice.
Mix soup, sour cream and parsley and pour over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers and add to pan juices, then sprinkle on top of chicken.
Bake covered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Take cover off and cook for 5 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Melt butter with strawberries.
Mash in.
Mix in powdered sugar until spreading consistency.

title: friendship cake made with 30 day fruit starter
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in glass container and cover loosely. Store at room temperature. Stir 2 or 3 times the first day and once a day thereafter. At the end of 2 weeks, the starter is ready to use for making 30 Day Cake.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Line cookie sheet with graham crackers. Boil butter, margarine and sugar for 2 minutes. Pour over graham crackers; sprinkle on nuts. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool, then break apart. Store in airtight container.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Combine all except milk.
Cook on low for 6 hours.
Take out ham bone and chop up ham.
Put ham back in and add milk.
Cook 1/2 hour more.
Add more water or milk if too thick.

title: russian chicken
directions: In
a bowl, mix dressing, soup mix and apricots together. Place
chicken
breasts
in
large
casserole dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake in oven at 425° until done.

title: beet pickles
directions: Pour boiling syrup over beets. Seal. Cold pack 1/2 hour in boiling water.
This fills 3 quarts of beets.
These can be used for Harvard beets also.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Toss together the first 6 ingredients.
Cook the hamburger; drain.
Add the kidney beans.
Mix together the lettuce and hamburger mixtures.
Add the crushed Doritos taco flavored corn chips and toss.
Garnish with 1 sliced avocado before serving.

title: lazy day cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars.
Add vanilla, eggs, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add flour.
Roll dough into balls; flatten on greased cookie sheet with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Great, easy sugar cookies.

title: meatballs
directions: Place all ingredients, except ground beef and oatmeal in blender.
Blend well.
Add blended ingredients to ground beef and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into meatballs.
Either fry in a small amount of shortening or bake for 35 to 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
Meatballs may be served plain or served in a spaghetti sauce.
Makes about 30 one-inch meatballs.

title: cottage pudding short cake
directions: Beat with electric mixer in order given.
Pour in regular cake pan.
Bake at 375°
until golden brown.
When it draws away a little around the cake pan it is done.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all in 1 bowl and stir well.
Pour into 2 graham pie crusts.
Refrigerate them.

title: copper pennies(carrots)
directions: Cook carrots until almost tender. Drain.
Mix the ingredients above together and pour over top of the carrots, onions and pepper.
Let sit overnight. Will keep up to 3 weeks.

title: my mother's cinnamon bread
directions: Make plain biscuit dough and roll thin.
Spread with thick white sauce and sprinkle with ground boiled ham.
Roll like jelly roll.
Chill before cutting.
Slice thin.
Can be sprinkled with paprika.
Bake in hot oven until crisp.

title: cottage herb rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, oregano and salt; mix well. Cut in cold butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Blend in cheese, egg and yeast mixture. Turn onto well floured surface; knead. Shape into ball; place in greased bowl.

Brush top with melted butter; cover and let rise until doubled. Punch down; shape as desired. Brush with melted butter; cover. Let rise again until nearly doubled. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Serve while warm.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme together well. Chill. Serve with assorted fresh fruits.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in casserole dish.
Place cheese over broccoli and chicken.
Mix soup and milk; pour over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Put onions on top of casserole.
Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: christmas carrots
directions: Peel carrots.
Cut diagonally.
Cook for 20 minutes and set aside.

title: jane's never fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except peanut butter, in a medium size pot.
Bring to a hard boil until sugars are melted, about 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter.
Cook just until all are melted and mixed good.
Pour in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cut when cool.
I have never had a failure.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In large bowl beat eggs, add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Fold in cheese, spinach and onion salt. Spread in dish.
Cook 35 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
This is a good dip for broccoli or cauliflower.

title: pork chop pear bake
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Coat chops with mixture of the flour, 3/4 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Brown chops on both sides in hot oil.
Place chops in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Drain pears.
Reserve 1/2 cup syrup.
Set pears aside.
Pour syrup over meat.
Cover; place in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Add pears; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cook until heated through, 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal chippers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk; beat well.
Add flour and oats; mix.
Add chips and nuts; mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.
These cookies freeze well.
Or, you can freeze the dough in rolls, then thaw, slice and bake as needed.
Makes 4 dozen or more, depending on size.

title: fluffy boiled icing
directions: Combine sugar, water, and syrup in saucepan.
Stir until well blended.
Boil slowly without stirring until mixture will spin a long thread when a little is dropped from a spoon.
Hold spoon high above the saucepan (238° to 242° F).

title: cobblestones
directions: Melt butter and chocolate bits in double boiler.
Mix egg and confectioners sugar.
Put melted chocolate bits and butter into egg mixture.
Add 4 cups miniature marshmallows and 1/2 cup nuts. Roll in coconut; place in refrigerator and serve cold.

title: caribbean fruit cake
directions: Mix Jell-O with juice and water.
Cool until begins to thicken. Add all the other items.
Mix and refrigerate until congealed.
Add tablespoon mayonnaise or spread top with mayonnaise.

title: spinach tarta
directions: Cook 3 pkgs. spinach - drain - add all other ingredients to the hot spinach except the third egg.
Spread in large pan (use at least a 9 in. x 13 in.)
Take the third egg and lightly beat, spread on top of mixture.
Do not cover pan.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 35 - 45 minutes or until it is well set (firm to touch).

title: shortbread pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, measure all ingredients except cocoa.
With hands, knead until well blended.
Set aside half of the dough.
Knead cocoa into dough remaining in bowl.
Wrap each in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until dough is firm enough to roll (or place dough in freezer for 40 minutes).
On sheet of waxed paper, with floured rolling pin, roll half of the chocolate dough into an 8 x 6-inch rectangle.
On another sheet of wax paper, do same with plain dough.
Invert plain dough onto chocolate dough.
Discard wax paper.
Starting at 8-inch side, roll dough jelly roll fashion. Wrap roll in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 2 hours until firm enough to slice (or freeze 40 minutes).
Repeat with remaining dough.
Slice one roll crosswise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place slices about 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove cookies to wire racks to cool. Repeat with remaining roll.
Store in tightly covered container. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in pan; bring to boil for 1 minute. Add powdered sugar, vanilla and peanut butter; beat until smooth. Add oats; beat well.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Then mix in tortilla chips, chopped olives, tomato and shredded cheese.
You may also add salsa and/or sour cream for a spicy flavor.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour into greased casserole dish. Cover with grated sharp cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: philadelphia cream cheese pie
directions: Blend together and pour into chilled graham cracker crust. Ice with Dream Whip and chill until serving.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni per directions on box.
Layer macaroni, sauce and cheese alternately in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish, ending with cheese.
Toss crumbs on top with melted butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 375° until sauce is bubbly and crumbs browned.

title: slush
directions: Add tea bags to boiling water.
Mix all ingredients; store 24 hours in freezer.
Stir after 12 hours.
Add Sprite and a cherry to serve.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; saute onion.
Mix bacon and all three beans together and add mustard, vinegar, brown sugar, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake, covered, until most of liquid is cooked off, about 45 minutes, at 350°.

title: yummy squash casserole
directions: Slice squash; cook until tender; drain and mash.
Measure squash after it is cooked.
Add butter, salt, pepper and milk.
Mix all together.
Add beaten eggs, onion, cheese and crackers.
Pour into a buttered casserole and bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: microwave bean burrito
directions: Place 4 tortillas stacked between 2 damp paper towels. Microwave on High about 40 seconds.
Spread each tortilla with 1/4 fried beans. Top each evenly with shredded cheese.
Add a few slices of pickled jalapeno peppers. Fill in one side and roll up tortillas into tight cylinders.
Place seam down on greased microwave-safe platter. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High until heated through and cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Fry the bacon; drain most of the fat off.
Beat the egg, sugar and flour.
Add the vinegar and water.
Add to bacon; cook over medium heat.
It should be like a thin gravy.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Also, if you want it more sour, add more vinegar or, for sweeter, add more sugar.

title: spinach supreme(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: twinkie pudding
directions: Cut twinkies in half lengthwise.
Line a trifle bowl around the sides and on the bottom with twinkie halves with the filling facing inside the bowl.
Combine the prepared vanilla pudding, Eagle Brand milk, 1/2 of the Cool Whip and banana slices in a large bowl.
Pour mixture into trifle bowl all the way to the top of the twinkies.
Chill for at least 6 to 8 hours to set.
When ready to serve, put the remainder of the Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nutmeg.
A yummy summer treat!

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Set Coke out to get to room temperature.
Warm up juice from the bing cherries and juice from the crushed pineapple until it is hot.
Pour the above into a bowl with the two packages of Jello. Cut up cream cheese and put in Jello.
Put in pineapple.
Add cherries.
Cut pecans up very small and add.
After above is cooled, then pour in the Coke.
Pour into molds or dish and refrigerate until set.
Remove jello from mold and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix pineapple, fruit cocktail, oranges and pudding mix. Add Cool
Whip.
Pour
into deep dish; sprinkle with nuts and coconut. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, onion, peas, cheese and eggs.
Cover completely with mayonnaise; spread Parmesan cheese over top, then the bacon pieces.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, sour cream, pepper, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of onions with potatoes.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown chops.
Lay on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350°, covered, 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove cover.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions over chops.
Bake additional 10 minutes.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and oil for 2 minutes. Cool. Rinse and drain beans.
Add to liquid.
Add the
other ingredients. Marinate several hours.

title: tidbits
directions: Mix all ingredients in a "large" roasting pan.
Pour 2 cubes melted margarine on top.
Stir well.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes. Stir every 10 minutes.

title: orange tapioca dessert
directions: Mix together tapioca pudding, orange jello, and water.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from stove and cool.
Add mandarin oranges, pineapple, and Cool Whip.
Mix together and refrigerate.
Can be put in a 9x13 dish and sprinkled with nuts.

title: carolyn's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well and add other ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake in slow oven (325°) for about 45 to 60 minutes or until firm and golden brown.

title: quick chocolate angel
directions: Cut or break cake into bite size pieces.
Gently fold fudge sauce into Cool Whip.
Place 1/2 of cake pieces into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish (or larger, depending on cake size).
Spread 1/2 Cool Whip mixture on cake pieces.
Add remaining pieces and spread remaining Cool Whip mixture on top.
Chill or use immediately.

title: bebe's caramel cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, add eggs, beating well, then flavoring.
Add milk alternately with flour (starting and ending with flour).
Beat well, pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions until clear and mix with all other ingredients into the onions. Use with pork or chicken.

title: layered salad
directions: Chop purple onion; add sugar and set aside.
Layer lettuce first and then place purple onion and sugar on top of lettuce. Next, layer green pepper, celery, mushrooms and peas.
Cover the top with mayonnaise, then place shredded cheese on top.
Chill overnight.

title: pizza macaroni bake
directions: Set the cheese packet from dinner mix aside. In a saucepan, bring water to boil. Add macaroni; cook for 8-10 minutes or until tender. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook the beef, onion and green pepper over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Drain macaroni; stir in the contents of cheese packet. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheddar cheese. Top with beef mixture, pizza sauce and pepperoni and mozzarella cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until heated through.

title: coffee lemon cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Blend in flour.
Add liquid ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a tube pan.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat and mix well the cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Top with more Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cabbage dish
directions: Put cabbage, butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk together and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add green pepper, onion, cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix all together and bake another 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and set aside.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Mix the two mixtures and add one cup chopped nuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Divide batter between them and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Bread freezes well.

title: joyce's stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together (including water that onions are soaked in) and heat.
Make a medium-thin paste with cornstarch and water and thicken to your liking.

title: marinated salmon fillets
directions: Marinate salmon fillets or steaks in mixture for several hours.
Broil or grill until fish flakes easily.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco until well blended.
Add eggs, mixing in well.
Stir in milk and flavorings.
Mix baking powder with flour and add gradually until well mixed.
Pour into a greased and floured angel food cake or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. The secret of this cake is the Crisco.

title: chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix together and spread in baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: valley forge cheesecake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Blend well.
Add sugar, cornstarch, flour, lemon, vanilla and eggs.
Beat with mixer until smooth. Add melted margarine.
Beat well.
Grease spring-form pan lightly and add mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° preheated oven. Then bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Turn oven off and crack door.
Leave in oven to cool.
(Raised cake will fall.)
Cool completely on counter.
Refrigerate overnight, at least.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs, corn, peppers, onions, cheese and bacon bits.
Fold in oil.
Cook in 350° oven until brown, about 20 or 30 minutes.
Cook in shallow greased pan.
You can cut back on eggs and oil.
Use Cheddar cheese.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and cut into 3/4-inch thick slices.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip tomato slices into flour mixture.
Heat butter in a 10-inch skillet.
Add tomato slices, cook over medium heat (turning once) until golden brown.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients and form into meatballs. Put in baking pan.
Boil together remainder of ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake for 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: "sweet" chex snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, mix cereal, nuts and coconut; set aside.
Over medium heat in a saucepan, mix sugar, Karo and butter; boil 3 minutes.
Pour over cereal and stir until well coated.
Spread over wax paper to dry and cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix apples, cinnamon and sugar.
Put into bottom of baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in another bowl and put over the apple mixture.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix together; roll into patties.
Deep fry in low or no fat oil until golden brown.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs and gradually add sugar. To last cup of sugar, add flour and nutmeg and mix well. Add butter and remaining ingredients, including squash. Divide mixture in pie shells. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until knife inserted comes out clean. Pie has consistency of sweet potato or custard pie.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll in mixture of sugars and cinnamon.
Grease Bundt pan. Drop biscuits into pan.
Melt margarine and pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in a greased 10 x 13-inch pan. Topping is two cups crushed cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted butter or oleo.
Mix together and put over top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vinegar butter sauce
directions: Heat ingredients together.
Serve hot over beets, spinach, cabbage, etc.
Enough for 4 servings.

title: margaret tabler's one dish supper
directions: Place hamburger over bottom of baking dish.
Press down evenly. Add drained potatoes, then onions and kidney beans.
Cover top layer with soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas, chicken, tomatoes and cucumber in 5-quart bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and curry powder and spread over salad.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle with croutons and bacon crumbs.
You can combine ham with the chicken in this recipe, which is very good.

title: juanita's lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in the upper top of a double boiler.
Add the water; stir and cook over direct heat until thickened.
Place top pan in lower part of the boiler which contains the right amount of water.
Cover top pan and cook for 15 minutes.

title: peach tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well and store in an airtight container.
To serve, stir about 2 teaspoons mix into 8 ounces hot water.
Yield:
about 3 1/2 cups tea mix.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes; let cool.
Add to chilled orange, lemon and pineapple juices.
Pour over ice in punch bowl. Add ginger ale.
Float scoops of sherbet on top.
Serves 40.

title: fresh mushroom soup
directions: Slice 1/2 of mushrooms.
Finely chop remaining mushrooms; set aside.
Melt butter in a Dutch oven.
Add onion and brown sugar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 15 minutes.
Add all mushrooms and saute 5 minutes.
Add flour, stirring until smooth. Gradually add water, broth and vermouth.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in salt and pepper.
Yields 6 cups.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper. Drain and set aside. Mix cornmeal, milk, eggs, creamed corn and jalapeno pepper juice. Grease iron skillet and layer the following: 1/2 batter, ground beef, grated onion, jalapenos, grated cheese and 1/2 batter. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: enchiladas
directions: Take cooked ground beef and add taco seasoning; mix well.
Set aside.
Place 1 spoonful of ground beef, chili beans and grated cheese in a tortilla shell.
Roll up and place in a long casserole dish.
Cover with sauce.
After all done, add rest of grated cheese.
Cook at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: marinated water chestnuts
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in soy sauce for 1 hour.
Cut bacon into thirds.
Drain water chestnuts and roll in sugar.
Wrap each chestnut with bacon and secure with toothpick.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
(Turn after 15 minutes.)
Drain and serve warm.

title: zucchini-carrot cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350° to 375°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.

Beat together butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy. Fold in flour, cinnamon, then fold in zucchini, nuts and carrots. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and cook about 10 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top, if desired.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: "meant to be" cheese danish
directions: Prepare the oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into ball.
Roll with fresh chopped parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: chocolate icing(best ever)
directions: Put all ingredients in a large saucepan.
When mixture comes to a boil, cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and set on cooling rack.
Let cool until hand temperature on bottom of pan. Beat to spreading consistency.
Yields enough icing for 2 or 3 layers.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Let seeds soak in salt water overnight.
Drain; pat dry. Spread on baking sheet sprayed with Pam and bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: rice with green peas
directions: Saute rice, onion and caraway seed in butter in a Dutch oven 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken broth, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add green peas and cook 5 minutes.

title: pastry for eclairs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Melt margarine and water.
Bring to a boil.
Turn off heat.
Add flour and salt.
Stir until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir until smooth and shiny. Use a tablespoon of dough.
Form into desired shape.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Pastry is done when dough is dry inside.
Cool and fill with Eclair Filling.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: In large dish, combine gelatin with boiling water.
Fold in all at once the strawberries with juice, bananas, pineapple and walnuts.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or mold.
Let set until firm (in freezer is quicker).
Keep other half until ready to use, but do not let it set.
After first half is firm, spread sour cream on next.
Add last half of gelatin mixture; let stand in refrigerator.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: In large saucepan, combine ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 10 minutes. Remove spices. Serve warm.

title: raspberry and black cherry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add blueberries and pineapple, well drained.
Chill until set.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Sprinkle shrimp with Tony's seasoning. Set aside. Melt margarine and saut onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic. Add flour and parsley. Cook slowly. Do not brown. Add tomato soup and 1 can of water. Cook together 20 to 30 minutes. Add shrimp. Cook 10 minutes. Set aside 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Make a well in the middle, then add next 3 ingredients. Pour into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm or chilled with whipped cream.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in order given.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir just prior to serving.

title: pappaw's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onions and fry until tender and brown.
Cook potatoes until almost done.
Now in a very large cooker, put meat mixture and potatoes together.
Add all canned foods next and stir well.
Put in seasoning and stir all ingredients together until well mixed.
Put on stove and simmer for about 2 hours.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Slowly add juice; mix thoroughly. Pour into 9-inch graham cracker pie crust and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with a dollop of fresh whipped cream and lime zest garnish.

title: hamburger potato cheese pie
directions: Mix beef, salt, pepper, onion and egg with bread crumbs that have been soaked in milk.
Spread in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with potatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more and sprinkle with paprika.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
Add White Sauce.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Beat butter in a large bowl at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla. Combine flour, soda and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating until blended.
Cover and chill one hour.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on a well floured surface.
Cut 2 1/2-inch rounds. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes in 350° oven or until edges are lightly browned.

title: spareribs with barbecue sauce
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in frying pan.
Place spareribs in pan. Brown both sides of spareribs. Remove spareribs and place in casserole dish.
Put 1 tablespoon butter in frying pan with onions and simmer.
Add ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar. Simmer for 20 minutes. Stir often.
Pour this over spareribs.
Cook 45 minutes at 375°.

title: mel-o-dee's bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until blended.
Roll any size amount you wish in your hands.
Use powdered sugar on hands to keep mixture from sticking.
Place on cookie sheet, this can be made up a few days in advance, just refrigerate.

title: spring garden dinner
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, carrots and onions in semi-thin circles.
Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Start layering potatoes, carrots, onions, butter, salt and pepper in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
keep layering until vegetables are used. Pour 2 cans of tomatoes on top.
Bake 35 minutes on 400°.
Baking times may vary.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cheese. Add it just before you are ready to eat.
Pour Catalina dressing over salad.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Combine ingredients.
Make dough into small balls.
Bake at 400°
for 10 minutes on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
May be frozen ahead of time for parties.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar gradually.
Add 2 eggs (1 at a time) and beat constantly.
Add sour cream (keep beating). Add 4 eggs (1 at a time) and keep beating.
Stir from sides and bottom of bowl until mixed well.

title: hermits
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water and boil 5 minutes and cool. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs; add the dry ingredients. Drain raisins and add; then add the walnuts. Grease jelly roll pan. Spread batter over and bake in pan size 15 1/2 x 10 1/4 x 3/4-inches
in a
350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: nachos(may be made in quantity for large groups)
directions: Cook hamburger and taco seasoning according to directions; layer in baking dish with salsa and shredded cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over nacho chips.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk 1 hour.
Add egg and beat well. Add sugar; mix.
Add flour sifted with salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add cooled shortening.
Bake in greased muffin tins in hot oven (350° to 375°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni.
Drain.
On low heat, heat cut-up cheese and green pepper.
Stir constantly.
Add milk, a little at a time. The secret to the recipe is adding milk with cheese to get a small sauce.
The macaroni may appear soupy, but let it stand 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: peanut butter barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a boiler.
Stir on medium heat until all are mixed well.
Simmer on low.
Baste chicken, chops or ribs as needed.
Sauce will be very thin.

title: texas sheet cake(great for covered dish supper or group meetings)
directions: Bring margarine, milk and cocoa to a boil slowly.
Beat in sugar, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, sour cream and baking soda.
Pour into greased 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet with 1-inch rim.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pack lightly in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature. Loosen edges. Turn onto a platter. Serve with Mustard Dill Sauce. Serves 4 to 5.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in pot and saute onions until tender.
Add the flour and cook for 1 or 2 minutes more.
Add beef broth, water and next three ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Toast French bread on both sides.
Put bread in soup bowls and spoon soup over bread. Cover top of soup with Mozzarella cheese and brown under broiler. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Blend; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Cream the butter; blend in cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Spread frosting over top and sides of cake.
Spread 2 cups coconut over top and sides of cake.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook the brown sugar, butter and evaporated milk until thick and brown.
Mix the quart of milk, flour and egg yolks and add to the sugar mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pie shells.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, raw peanuts and Karo syrup for 4 minutes on High. Cook 4 more minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Mix well and cook 1 or 2 minutes longer.
Add soda; stir.
Pour out on large piece of foil sprayed with Pam.
Cool and break.
Store in airtight container.

title: oneida's cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients together.
Mix well.
Shape into ball or log and roll in dried ham or dried beef (shredded).
Some people prefer nuts instead of shredded ham.
Serve with crackers.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add vanilla and water and mix.
Add salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix.
Stir in flour until stiff.
Add nuts.
Make a roll of the dough.
Let stand overnight.
Flour roll so it doesn't stick to board.
Slice and bake at 375°
for 10 or 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: yellow-haired girl salad
directions: Wash lettuce leaf and pat dry with paper towel.
Lift 1 peach half from can and 1 maraschino cherry from jar with fork and place on paper towel to dry.
(Refrigerate remaining peaches and cherries with syrup for another time.)
Wash 1 celery stalk and pinch off leaves.
Cut the celery into thin strips about 2-inches long and 1/4-inch wide on cutting board.
Keep 4 strips for your salad.
(Refrigerate the rest for nibbles.)

title: chocolate slush cake
directions: Step 1:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Heat milk and butter until butter melts.
Beat eggs and mix together.
Add all ingredients together in a bowl.
Let mixture sit for about 30 minutes.
This gives the pudding a better taste. Pour into a buttered dish and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
When done, it will be all puffed up and brown.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut squash in half.
Peel and remove seeds.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Stir together remaining ingredients except apples.
Arrange squash in ungreased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches).
Top with apple slices. Sprinkle sugar mixture over the top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cranberries and lemon juice in mixer.
Place in 5-cup salad mold; freeze.
Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise; gradually add powdered sugar.
Fold in nuts, pineapple and whipped cream. Top salad mold.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 8.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Turn off burner but leave syrup on burner until bubbling stops.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage; chop onion and pepper.
Add celery salt and seed and dill weed.
Bring to boil the sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and dry mustard.
Pour hot liquid over vegetables.
Do not stir until chilled.
Can be made day before or a few hours before used.

title: "fabulous" salad
directions: Drain beets.
Mix all ingredients together in order given. (You can use all sour cream and no mayonnaise, if preferred.) Salad is better if made day before so all flavors can blend. Yield: 8 to 12 servings.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend all together.
Add just a dash of Worcestershire sauce and a little of onion.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Wipe pork chops with a damp paper towel.
Trim excess fat. In a large skillet, heat butter.
Mix flour and salt.
Coat pork chops on both sides; brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add garlic, onion, green pepper, celery, thyme, sugar and hot sauce.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Bring to boiling and return the chops to the skillet.
Spoon sauce over chops and simmer, covered, 40 to 50 minutes until tender.
Serve with rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southern baked beans
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, layer beans, chili sauce, 4 strips of bacon, brown sugar and mustard.
Top with 4 strips bacon. Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
If too stiff, add a little milk.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda and add to creamed mixture and eggs.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: moms grape pie
directions: Remove and save the grape skins.
Put pulp in saucepan without water.
Bring to a rolling boil.
While hot, rub through a sieve to remove seeds.
Mix strained pulp with skins.
Combine remaining ingredients, mix well. Add this mixture to the grapes. Pour this into a pastry lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake 35 - 45 minutes in a hot oven.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes. Then poke holes down through cake.
Combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup coconut in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 minute. Spoon over cake.
Cool.
Fold in 1/2 cup coconut into whipped topping and spread over cake.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chuck; add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain; set aside.
Cook noodles in boiling water.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Combine meat, noodles, mushrooms, onion, tomato sauce, cheese and all but 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour into two greased 2-quart casserole dishes.
Top with reserved Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
You may freeze if you like.

title: pot cheese cookies
directions: Grease and flour cookie sheets.
Cookies should be light brown on bottom and white on top.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add pot cheese, almond flavoring, flour and other ingredients.
Dough will be sticky.
Use two spoons to spoon into pan, not too much.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes approximately 100 cookies.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt last three ingredients and boil 5 minutes; add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour over mixture of dry ingredients and bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour on cookie sheets or oven racks that have been lined with aluminum foil.
Cool in large bowl or countertop which has been sprayed with Pam. Occasionally break up mixture as it cools.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in buttered casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix.
Drop into 6 cup muffin tin, well greased.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: amish cookies
directions: Mix.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven.
Makes 17 dozen.

title: corn fritters
directions: Heat 1/2-inch of oil in electric skillet to 400°.
In bowl with fork, stir 1 tablespoon oil and next 6 ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon into oil.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes, turning once.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: strawberry pineapple dessert
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar. Then add the strawberries and pineapple. The pineapple and strawberries do not get drained. Use juice of both. Add the pecan bits and pieces. Then fold in the Cool Whip. Freeze.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole. Top with bread crumbs or cornflake crumbs.
Drizzle butter over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. This dish freezes well.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar, margarine together and press in bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: baby apple pancake
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add apples, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Saute until tender.
Reserve.
Combine eggs, milk, flour, granulated sugar and salt in a blender or food processor. Whirl until smooth.
Butter inside of a 12-inch skillet with ovenproof handle.
Pour in batter.
Spoon apple mixture evenly over top.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 20 minutes or until pancake is puffy and golden brown.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars in heavy pan.
Add Eagle Brand milk and syrup. Stir well.
Add milk and vanilla to fill 4-quart freezer.
Fill freezer with ice and salt.
Should freeze in approximately 40 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: grandma irene's summer sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix once a day for 3 days. On the 4th day, pack tight into rolls.
Bake on a rack at 140° for 10 to 12 hours.
Do not make substitutions.
Can be frozen.

title: apple cream coffee cake
directions: Combine nuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter; gradually add remaining sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; add to cream mixture alternately with sour cream, beating well after each addition.
Spread half of batter in a well-greased 10-inch tube pan with a removable bottom.
Top with apple slices; sprinkle with half of the nut mixture.
Top with remaining batter, then remaining nut mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, until cake tests done.
Remove from oven; let stand for 30 minutes.
Loosen sides of cake.
Lift cake with removable bottom from pan; cool.
Before serving, carefully lift cake from pan. Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time; mix well after each egg.
Sift flour and baking soda; add to butter mixture, alternating with sour cream and lemon juice.
Blend until smooth.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour batter into well-greased and lightly floured pound cake or Bundt cake pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Serve after cooled.
"Nice with French vanilla ice cream."

title: chocolate yum-yum
directions: Mix and mash flat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes at 350° (don't let this get brown).
Cool.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Whip cream cheese and sugar together.
Fold in whipped cream. Add crushed pineapple (drained).
Pour in pie shell and let chill 2 hours.

title: sparkling grape punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; stir.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Stir in juices.
Chill.
Before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion and green pepper until onions are transparent. Stir in rest of ingredients; pour into greased casserole dish. Cover and bake 1 hour at 375°.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Makes 2 pies.
Beat eggs; add sugar, margarine, 1/2 cup of milk and flavoring.
Add meal to the rest of milk and let it set a minute.
Add to mixture and stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chrusciki(angel wings)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide dough into 3 pieces.
Roll out one ball thin.
Cut into one-inch wide and 3-inches long strips.
Cut a slit in the center and make a bow tie; repeat with remainder of dough.
When all made, heat Crisco, deep fry in large skillet on one side and then the other.
Sprinkler with powdered sugar.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done; spread bread with butter and cube. Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place bread cubes in bottom.
Sprinkle crumbled sausage over bread. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and mustard.
Pour over baking dish.
Chill for 5 hours.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Can be made before hand and frozen before baking.

title: low-fat banana chocolate chip mini muffins
directions: In large bowl combine eggs, applesauce, bananas and Equal measure.
Mix in flour mixture; alternate with milk.
Stir in nuts (optional) and chocolate chips.
Pour into mini muffin tins, sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: cracker candy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Place saltine crackers on foil.
Mix margarine and brown sugar in sauce pan and heat to a boil.
Boil and stir 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers and bake 5 minutes or until crackers float.
Remove from oven and sprinkle 8 ounce package of chocolate chips over crackers.
Spread while hot.
Cool.
Break into pieces and keep in freezer.

title: boy friend cookies
directions: Stir butter and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Then stir in flour, soda and vanilla.
Add oats, peanuts and chocolate bits.
Mix well but don't beat.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter, white sugar and brown sugar.
Mix eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Mix all together and add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts. Mound loosely onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: chicken walnut stir-fry
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon Crisco oil, 2 teaspoons soy sauce and 1 teaspoon cornstarch in small mixing bowl.
Add chicken.
Stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate about 30 minutes.
Mix chicken broth, ginger, remaining 3 teaspoons soy sauce and remaining 2 teaspoons cornstarch in small bowl.
Set aside.
Heat remaining 4 tablespoons Crisco oil in large skillet or wok. Add refrigerated chicken mixture and red pepper.
Stir-fry over medium-high heat until chicken is no longer pink.
Remove chicken from skillet. Set aside.
Add onion and garlic to skillet.
Stir-fry until tender.
Add chicken and chicken broth mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in walnuts.
Serve with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: jello mold
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove. Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Add to pineapple mix and cool. Soften cream cheese; add cherries and mix well.
Combine mixtures.
Whip heavy cream.
Fold into combined mixtures.
Put in long loaf pan and refrigerate overnight.

title: special k loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a greased 8-inch casserole dish for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Let set for a few minutes before serving.

title: dessert
directions: Combine pudding and cool whip.
Add fruit and marshmallows. Refrigerate.

title: apples yum yum
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 9-inch pan and grease.
Mix brown sugar, oatmeal and flour with margarine in a bowl.
Spread apples in pan.
Spread crust mixture over apples.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yields 9 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch pan; level mixture.
Over the top sprinkle the cake mix.
Top with bits of oleo.
Sprinkle shredded coconut over mixture plus the walnuts. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: funnel cakes
