directions: Stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Beat together
the
milk
and
egg,
then
blend in the flour mixture, beating
just
until
smooth.
Let
stand
about
10 minutes. Heat
about
1/2 inch of oil in a deep skillet until very
hot, about
Drizzle
the batter in a thin stream into the hot oil, starting in the center and spiraling out to desired size. Fry
on both sides until golden brown, about 35 seconds per side. Drain on paper sides and serve immediately, sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Makes 6 (6-inch) cakes.

title: russian coffee cake
directions: Bring to a boil the brewed coffee and margarine.
Stir in oatmeal.
Let mixture cool.
Mix together sugars, cinnamon, nutmeg, eggs, flour and soda.
Add flour-sugar mixture to oatmeal mixture.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar.

title: german streusel kuchen
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together with fork until crumbly.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
Cream together remaining oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients into creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat until bubbles appear. Mixture should not be too stiff.
Pour into two greased and floured cake tins.
Sprinkle prepared streusel topping over batter.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Fresh plums, apples or peaches can be sliced and arranged on batter before adding the streusel topping.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all cheeses, blend well.
Shape into balls. Refrigerate, roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk; stir only until dry ingredients are moist.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Cook on sheet at 450° for 10 minutes.
May be frozen after cutting and baked as needed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Add bacon and mix all.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in oven 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken ole
directions: Cook chicken in microwave until done.
Cool and cut in large chunks.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch squares or strips.
Mix soups, milk and onion.
Add salsa.
Butter large baking dish.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons juice from chicken to bottom of dish.
Place layer of tortillas on bottom, layer chicken, diced chilies on top.
Spoon sauce mix over top and cheese.
Repeat layers 2 to 3 times, end with sauce.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate 24 hours or freeze. Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: nancy's glorified pork chops
directions: Flour pork chops.
Brown pork chops on both sides.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
On top of each pork chop, place 1/4 cup of dressing.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup and onion.
Pour over pork chops and dressing.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
I cover with foil.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and top with vanilla ice cream.

title: italian cheese balls
directions: Combine cheese, onions, cracker meal, bread crumbs, walnuts, garlic salt, chili powder, salt and eggs.
Make into balls using scoop.
Deep fry at 350° for 3 minutes or until light brown. Place in sprayed pan.
Cover with sauce of equal amounts of catsup and jelly or jam.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: granny's chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until set about 350° to 375°.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes.
For deep-dish pie crust, increase mixture by 1/2 more.

title: sour cream santa cookies(these are fun to do with the kids.)
directions: Cream Crisco; gradually add sugar and cream until light.
Add eggs and sour cream and set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt; add vanilla to first mixture and blend all together and chill 2 hours.
Roll out dough and cut with floured cookie cutters.
Use Wondra flour to roll out dough so you don't pick up excess flour.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, 10 to 12 minutes if rolled out thick.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill dough for 1/2 hour.
Roll dough into 1 inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place balls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Do not flatten.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook between 350° and 375° until chicken is done.
Cut potatoes in half or quarters.
Cut carrots in half.
Dice or cut onions as rings.
Pour in water until it almost covers chicken.
Put in spices.
Cook for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; press into Pyrex dish 9 x 13-inches.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix the Cool Whip, confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Spread mixture on crust after it cools, then prepare filling.
Combine blueberries, sugar, lemon juice and cornstarch.
Cook.
Cool.
Spread over cream cheese layer; top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour together.
Add egg yolks and milk. Cook until this thickens.
Pour into pie crust and beat egg whites.
Add them to pie and brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg.
Mix together dry ingredients, then add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add applesauce and raisins.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Saute onion and oleo.
Add to broccoli; mix well.
Add rice and soup.
Fold in Cheez Whiz.
Stir until cheese is melted and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch, well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop delight
directions: Coat chops with Shake 'N Bake.
Place in a baking pan; bake at 400° until brown.
Remove from oven; drain off all fat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and skin chicken.
Mix 1 stick butter and stuffing mix; put in casserole dish.
Tear chicken up in small pieces and place on top of stuffing mixture.
Mix mushrooms, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and 1 cup chicken broth.
Pour on top of chicken.
Mix 1/4 cup broth and 2/3 cup stuffing.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower with cheese sauce
directions: Bring 1-inch of water to a boil with 1/2 teaspoon salt in a medium saucepan.
Add cauliflower.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes; drain and keep warm.
Melt butter in small saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour, remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and paprika, if desired.
Cook and stir 3 minutes or until bubbly.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until smooth and thick. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Arrange cauliflower on a platter and spoon cheese sauce over top.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer until thick.
Pour into pie crust and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: gay's shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Mix dry ingredients, add vanilla, nuts and butter.
Mix just enough to get all ingredients blended.
Pour into pie plate and bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Serve with Cool Whip or French vanilla ice cream.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Stir wine and juice together in saucepan to dissolve juice. Add berries, turn burner on high, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add ginger and nutmeg.
Cool in serving dish.
Regrigerate.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Stir and set aside.
In a large skillet sprayed with nonstick spray, over medium-high heat, add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally.
Cook about 3 minutes, then add onion and bell pepper and continue cooking about 2 minutes.
Pour the sauce mixture and cook an additional 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Serve with rice or angel hair noodles. Serves 4.

title: diabetes zesty slaw
directions: Thoroughly mix mayonnaise and horseradish.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until fruit and cabbage are evenly coated with mayonnaise/horseradish mixture.
Chill for an hour before serving.

title: french coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well between additions.
Add vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Alternately add sifted ingredients and sour cream to mixture; blend together.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix butter, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and flour together.
Roll out on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until it begins to turn golden. Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup powdered and sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cooled crust and cut into 2-inch squares.
Top with fruit.

title: mini-blinis
directions: *Four tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon should be mixed together for rolling bread.

title: pork `n' veggie packets(for the grill)
directions: Divide pork, broccoli, carrots, water chestnuts, green pepper and onions evenly among 4 pieces of double-layered heavy-duty foil (18 x 12). Combine the soy sauce, sesame oil and ginger. Drizzle over pork and vegetables. Fold foil around filling and seal tightly. Grill, covered, over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender and pork is no longer pink. Serve with rice, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: hamburgers(charbroiled or grilled)
directions: Combine egg and bread, let soak 1 minute.
In large bowl add ground meat, bread and egg mixture, and all remaining ingredients. Mix together, pat down and let sit for 2 hours at room temperature or refrigerated overnight.
Make into 4 patties.

title: old-fashioned fudge
directions: Combine dry
ingredients
thoroughly in a heavy 4 quart saucepan.
Stir in milk and bring to a bubbly boil over medium heat,
stirring
constantly.
Boil without stirring until 234° (soft ball	stage).
Remove
from
heat
and
add
butter
and vanilla.
Do not
stir
in.
Let
stand
to
110°.	Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan and cool.
Yields approximately 3 dozen squares.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until firm.

title: fried apples
directions: Wash, core and slice into rings or quarters, but do not peel, the apples.
Place them in a heavy skillet in which fat has been melted.
Cover and cook over moderate heat until soft (5 to 10 minutes); then uncover and sprinkle with sugar and cook uncovered until the apples are delicately browned on under side.
If overcooked, the apples will fall to pieces.
Lift out carefully with a pancake turner.
Serve hot.
Makes 5 servings.

title: ragu chicken
directions: Bone and skin chicken.
Fry brown.
Place chicken in crock-pot; top with cheese.
Pour Ragu sauce over chicken and cook on low 4 hours.
Eat over cooked rice or noodles.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and add graham cracker crumbs.
Work until they are damp.
Press in bottom of container.
Beat egg. Add soft stick of margarine and sugar.
Spread this over crumb mixture.
Top this with bananas and pineapple.
Then spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with fine, chopped pecans.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight before serving.

title: roasted red pepper dip
directions: In blender or food processor, blend mayonnaise, red peppers and basil until smooth.
Stir in sour cream.
Cover and chill. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: easy candied dill strips
directions: Drain liquid from pickles.
Rinse in cold water and wipe dry. Slice pickles lengthwise in strips.
Return to jar and invert to drain remaining juice.
In saucepan, cook 4 cups sugar and 1 cup vinegar for 5 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes and pour over pickles.
Add celery seed and mustard seed to jar.
Replace lid, invert jar back and forth as pickles cool.
Refrigerate for 24 hours, inverting several times over that time.
Great, inexpensive and delicious!

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and dice stems.
Set caps aside. Melt margarine.
Mix stems, crabmeat, cheese and Italian bread crumbs together.
Add margarine to dry mixture to hold mixture together.
Stuff mushroom caps with crabmeat mixture.
Cook for approximately 15 to 20 minutes on 300° in conventional oven or until cheese melts or mushrooms are thoroughly heated.
May microwave also.
May freeze prior to cooking to use at later date.

title: singapore noodle salad
directions: Cut into 1/2-inch thick slices and dip in soy sauce.
Place on a lightly oiled cookie sheet. Sprinkle with garlic and black pepper.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cut into strips when cool.

title: cheese squares
directions: Beat ingredients until smooth.
Trim crusts off day-old bread; cut into 4 pieces.
Ice top and sides with mixture, not bottom. Bake until heated through in a 350° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put cut up cooked chicken in bottom of 13 x 9 casserole dish. Add package of California medley.
Spread can of cream of potato soup over vegetables.
Top with cheese.
Roll out croissant rolls and cut into strips.
Put on top of cheese and mixture as lattice shape.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cover with foil until last 10 minutes of baking.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix well. Pour over potatoes and mix well.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; drain all excess water from spinach.
Slice onions.
Chop water chestnuts.
Combine all ingredients and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: honey yogurt dip
directions: Put in a bowl and mix together.
Dip fresh fruit into dip.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir in all other ingredients, except Doritos chips and cheese.
Layer chips, meat mixture and cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until bubbly.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and rinse under cold water.
Add rest of ingredients and let chill.
Add tomatoes just before serving.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Puree all ingredients in blender until creamy.
Give in decorative container for gift.

title: fish casserole
directions: Boil haddock; remove bones and skin.
Place in buttered casserole dish in small pieces.
Add a bit of water the fish was cooked in.
Cover with 3 hard-boiled eggs, sliced.
Add a layer of American cheese (3 slices, cut in small pieces).
Mix soup with milk and add 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour this mixture over the top.
Cover the top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: festive hash and eggs
directions: Spread hash in 4 individual casseroles.
Make a depression in each with back of spoon.
Break one egg into each.
Do not season. Spoon 2 tablespoons milk over each; top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until almost set 18 to 20 minutes.
Top with paprika; let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in well-greased cast-iron skillet.
Spread cheese on top.
Add rest of mix over that.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: quick chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into thin strips; brown in hot oil along with the green pepper and onion.
Add all other ingredients except rice. Cook, stirring frequently, until vegetables are tender-crisp. Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water.
Fold in all at once strawberries (with juice drained), pineapple, bananas and walnuts. Put 1/2 mixture in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate until firm. Spread top with sour cream.
Spoon on remaining mixture and refrigerate until firm.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in oblong baking dish.
Top with 1 cup chow mein noodles or crushed potato chips.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Using punch bowl, crumble cake in bowl.
Mix pudding and pour half over cake. Next add 1/2 can of pineapple, 1 can strawberry pie filling and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Add Cool Whip and repeat with second layer of pineapple, strawberry pie filling, pecans and Cool Whip. Bananas may be added, if desired.

title: chocolate chip dessert
directions: At room temperature, work 1 package of dough into a glass baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour over dough.
Slice second package of chilled cookie dough and layer on top of cream cheese mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Chill completely before serving.
(Cuts easier if completely cold.)

title: chocoroons
directions: Blend butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add salt, soda and flour.
Blend.
Add chocolate chips and coconut.
Blend. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese.
Stir in pineapple (which has been well drained and blotted in paper towels).
Add 1 cup pecans, onions, peppers and salt.
Shape and chill overnight.
Half an hour before serving, roll in the remaining nuts.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt margarine in round glass baking pan or casserole in microwave.
Wash and dice celery.
Slice onion.
Add onion, celery and salt to margarine.
Cover with wax paper; cook for 8 minutes in microwave, until vegetables are tender.
Let cool.
Add broth and heat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Spread sour cream over chicken.
Spread soup (undiluted) over sour cream.
Crumble crackers; add poppy seed and 1 stick melted margarine.
Mix well. Crumble crackers over top of soup.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine eggs, milk and butter; add to flour mixture.
Add corn.
Drop by spoonful into hot fat (375°) for about 3 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 fritters.

title: easter bread
directions: Heat milk with margarine until lukewarm.
Add sugar.
Beat on low speed until blended.
Add dissolved yeast, 12 beaten eggs, salt, vanilla, orange juice and flour, 1 cup at a time.
(Dough is not stiff.)
Knead 3 to 4 minutes.
Cover well.
Set in a warm spot.
Let raise.
(Optional: May add raisins or mixed fruit.) Beat 1 egg white with a little water; brush on bread before baking.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: penuche fudge
directions: Add one-cup milk to sugar; boil until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Remove from stove and add butter and marshmallow. Beat well and add flavoring and nuts.
Beat until nearly stiff. Pour in pan and mark in squares.

title: berlin garlands
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter with confectioners sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and almond extract.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Chill several hours or overnight until dough is firm enough to handle.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Pinch off a level tablespoon of dough at a time and roll with the palm of your hands on a lightly floured pastry cloth until you have a log about 8 inches long.
Shape into a wreath, overlapping ends.
Place about 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheets.
Brush with beaten egg whites.
Press green and red candied cherries onto dough to resemble holly.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly golden.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool on wire racks.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown
ground beef and drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Mix in other ingredients and cook for 3 hours on low.

title: pizzicate pizzas
directions: Saute beef and onions until lightly browned; drain off excess fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce and oregano; heat to boiling point.
Flatten biscuits into 3-inch circles.
Spread with beef mixture; cover with sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Yields 20 small pizzas.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9-inch crust.
Cover with top crust and put 5 slits into top of crust.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds.
Pour into casserole. Top with 1/3 box Ritz crackers, crumbled and mixed with 1/2 stick margarine and 1/2 can almonds.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric beater.
Pour in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done (toothpick test).
Frost cake.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops.
Brown, not totally cooked.
Layer in casserole dish.
In 1st layer, add milk and cream of mushroom soup, then add in green beans and potatoes.
Slice an onion on top.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Chop onion and saute in butter.
Add soup, rice, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Put a thin layer of stuffing in bottom of dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into casserole. Sprinkle stuffing on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fettuccine alfredo(diabetic)
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan. Add garlic. Cook and stir 1 minute. Stir in flour. Gradually stir in milk. Cook until sauce thickens, stirring constantly. Add cheeses and pepper. Cook until melted. Serve on fettuccine; top with parsley. Makes 4 servings.

title: superb spoon bread
directions: Make a mush of the cornmeal, hot milk and salt.
Cook until thick; add beaten egg yolks, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Beat as when making meringue.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant 3/8-inch thick.
Beat egg and wine together.
Dip eggplant slices in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs and brown in oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Simmer tomato sauce, garlic and basil together in a saucepan, 10 to 15 minutes. Layer half the eggplant, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and sauce in a baking dish, then repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Break cake into bite-size pieces and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip. Alternate layers of cake and pudding mix.
Top with pie filling. Chill overnight and serve.

title: hawaiian luau pork (in oven)
directions: You will also need aluminum foil to wrap roast.

title: granny gibbs' famous dumplings
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to beaten eggs and milk. Roll and stretch each dumpling before dropping into hot broth, cooking until tender.
Serves 6.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Beat 2 minutes.
Use tube pan and bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool right side up for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; turn upside down.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Add coconut, dates, raisins and zucchini.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
While warm, frost with glaze and sprinkle with nuts.

title: brownie fudge nut pie
directions: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups nuts.
Heat milk, margarine and cocoa until margarine melts; remove from heat.
Stir in eggs, flour, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until center is firm.
Serve warm or cold garnished with whipped cream and remaining nuts.

title: spiced tea
directions: Put cinnamon and cloves in 1 quart water in pan.
Bring to boil.
Put tea into a tea holder or cloth.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and heat.

title: apple butter
directions: Quarter, core and peel apples.
Put in a large saucepan with the apple juice and cook over low heat, partly covered, until very soft, about 1 1/2 hours.
Puree in a food processor until very smooth.
Return to the saucepan and stir in sugar and spices. Cook, uncovered, over very low heat until dark brown and very thick, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking and burning.
Put in jars, cover and refrigerate up to 1 month.

title: low-fat green bean casserole
directions: Cut meat in half; wrap each 1/2 slice around 3 or 4 green beans and place in flat glass casserole dish.
When all meat is used up, pour dressing over casserole dish.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 24 hours ahead.
Next day, bake 30 minutes, covered, 30 minutes uncovered, at 350°.

title: peanut butter apple cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg, vanilla and apples.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients; mix thoroughly. Chill.
Mold into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable or chip dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese with mixer, then add other ingredients. Mix well.
Enjoy!

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Make a paste of vinegar, cocoa and food coloring; add to creamed mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to mixture, alternating with buttermilk. Add vanilla and blend thoroughly.
Pour into 3 (10-inch) pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy hot chili(microwave)
directions: In microwave cook ground beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown; drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, chili beans, catsup, jalapeno peppers, seasonings and water.
Cover and cook at full power 10 to 12 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.

title: cream cheese bread
directions: Heat sour cream over low heat; stir in sugar, salt, and oleo. Let cool. In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water and stir until it dissolves; add sour cream mixture; mix.
Add eggs and flour; mix well. Divide dough in 4 parts; roll out into 12 x 8 rectangles.

title: crab fettuccini
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in margarine until tender in a non-stick skillet.
Add flour, parsley, salt and pepper; cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add milk and cheese, stirring frequently to keep from sticking.
Add crab meat and cook for 15 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Fold in cooked noodles.
Pour into a casserole dish that has been sprayed with a non-stick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, carrots, then rest of dry ingredients and nuts. Bake in muffin pans 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine and spaghetti sauce. Shape into balls.
Brown the balls lightly in the margarine. Place in a casserole; cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked spaghetti or put in submarine roll for a meatball sandwich.

title: golden pineapple punch
directions: Freeze pineapple juice in can.
Remove juice about 1 hour before time to mix slush with fork.
Mix orange juice and lemonade with the amount of water on can.
Using large scoop, scoop sherbet.
Add ginger ale.
Stir.
Color may be added to juices.

title: apple dessert
directions: Line baking dish with cookies.
Cover with apple pie filling. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs. Add corn and flour. Add milk, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Melt oleo in casserole dish. Pour ingredients into baking dish. Bake at 400° until set.

title: lasagna
directions: In electric skillet, brown onions, garlic and hamburger. Drain fat.
Add sauce, oregano, salt, pepper and sugar; simmer for 20 minutes (covered skillet).
Cook noodles in meantime as directed; drain and chill noodles in cold water.
Arrange one portion of noodles in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with 1 portion sauce, 1 layer cheese; repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican meat with cornbread topping
directions: Cook meat until browned.
Add salt, garlic salt, pepper, chili powder, onion, tomatoes and rice.
Mix well.
Cook until thoroughly heated and liquid is absorbed.
Top with cornbread batter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: maxine's easy heart healthy dinner
directions: Dredge turkey patties in flour.
Slowly saute in margarine or oil.
While cooking, mix together and bring to a boil vegetable soup mix, can of tomatoes, water and yolkless noodles.
Serve on platter topped with turkey patties.
Garnish with sprigs of parsley.

title: west coast bouillabaisse
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onion, celery and garlic in oil for 3 minutes.
Stir in broth, tomatoes with juice, clams with juice, wine, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, Tabasco and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in shrimp, crab meat and halibut and cook for 5 minutes more.
Remove bay leaf.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: flank steak teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine the ingredients. Marinate flank steak overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally. Grill 7 minutes per side. Slice diagonally thin strips.

title: fried fish
directions: Wash fish and dry thoroughly. Dip into meal seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown fish in hot salad oil, using a deep iron pot heated by propane gas burner.

title: currant wine cordial
directions: Boil all ingredients until brittle when "tried" in cold water. Pour onto shallow dish to cool, then pull and flavor by adding extract while pulling.

title: chocanna
directions: Put chocolate ice cream, the banana and milk in the blender and you can add more milk to make the shake thick or you don't have to add more milk.

title: salsa
directions: Dice tomatoes, green peppers, hot peppers and onions.
Place in large pan.
Mince garlic.
Add to mixture in pan.
Heat on medium heat.
Add salt and pepper, sugar and tomato paste.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, then add wine vinegar.
Simmer 1/2 hour more.
Serve with nacho or tortilla chips.

title: bacon appetizer
directions: Crumble bacon.
Mix well with cheese, butter and caraway seed. Spread on Sociables savory crackers.
Place on a cookie sheet and broil about 4-inches from source of heat until cheese is melted. Remove and serve immediately.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix well and serve.
This shrimp butter is a chip dip.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except cranberries and nuts.
Sprinkle orange rind over batter and stir in.
Add cranberries and nuts; mix together.
Divide into 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate scotcheroos candy
directions: Combine sugar
and
corn
syrup
in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat,
stirring
frequently,
until
mixture begins to bubble. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well. Add Rice Krispies; stir until well
coated.
Press
mixture
into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt
chocolate and butterscotch morsels in top section of double boiler over hot,
but
not boiling water or in small saucepan over very low heat,
stirring constantly,
until
well mixed.
Remove from heat; spread evenly over
Rice Krispies mixture.
Cool until firm.
Cut into bars 2 x 1-inches.

title: broccoli cheese potato soup
directions: Heat broth, onion and frozen broccoli to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in potatoes until well blended; stir in remaining ingredients. Heat over low heat about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until hot and cheese is melted. Makes 12 servings.

title: cottage-tuna loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into buttered loaf pan. Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons dry bread crumbs and 1 teaspoon melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips. Sprinkle grated cheese over potato chip topping.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: sunday best roast beef
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Lightly flour each side.
Heat oil in large electric skillet.
Add crushed garlic cloves.
Brown roast on both sides.
Reduce heat.
Add onions.
Add 2 cups of water. Cover roast.
Cook on low heat for two hours or until done, adding water as needed.
Serve and accept the much deserved appreciation.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, mushroom soup and dry onion soup together.
Mix well; pour into an oblong casserole.
Prepare stuffing according to directions on box.
Pour stuffing over chicken mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: confetti holiday rounds
directions: Beat together the butter and sugar until creamy and fluffy. Add vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in pecans and cherries.

title: sparkling punch
directions: In a large punch bowl combine all the ingredients making sure to add ice and sherbet last.

title: chocolate chip banana nut bread
directions: Puree bananas.
Combine baking powder, baking soda, flour, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, sour cream, bananas, vanilla extract and banana extract to butter and sugar mixture; beat well.
Stir moist ingredients into dry ingredients.
(Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.) Add nuts and chocolate chips; mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan.
Decorate top with walnut halves.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until wire cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: party pizzaettes
directions: Roll each biscuit into a 4-inch circle; place on a greased baking sheet.
Spread a small amount of sauce on each biscuit.
Top with cheese and your favorite topping.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: betch can't eat one brownie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Beat and blend in chocolate syrup.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cheese casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
In large pan, mix cooked noodles, soups and milk.
May also add in optional ingredients.
Heat in pan or may put into casserole dish and heat later in microwave.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Blend cheese, sour cream and milk until smooth. Stir in rest of the ingredients, except nuts. Spoon into pie dish and sprinkle with nuts. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Mix well and bake in small muffin pans for 9 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Start with 1/2 cup Italian salad dressing (not creamy).
Can be fat-free. Mix all ingredients together.
Add more salad dressing, if desired.
Add the Parmesan cheese. Start with 1/2 cup and add more, if desired. Refrigerate overnight.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Dip each piece in melted margarine. Roll in crushed Ritz crackers.
Arrange chicken pieces in baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bread) together.
Cut off top of bread and hollow out the middle.
Use the bread pieces for dipping.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Grill your favorite meat, basting liberally with sauce.
It's great on skinless chicken pieces.

title: tingle bells punch
directions: Makes 40 (4 ounce) servings.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Make jello according to package directions, but use slightly less water than called for.
Gently stir in raspberries; chill. When jello is almost set, whip in Cool Whip and return to refrigerator until firmly set.
This is a very pretty and refreshing dessert.
(Fresh berries are delicious, too, when they're in season.)

title: two week candied sweet pickles
directions: Boil salt and 1 gallon water; pour over cucumbers in a crock jar.
Let stand 1 week.
Skim every day if necessary.
Second week, drain.
Heat 1 gallon fresh water and alum and pour over pickles in crock.
Do this for 3 days.
Fourth day, drain pickles. Heat vinegar, 5 cups sugar, box of stick cinnamon, celery seed and cloves.
Boil and pour over pickles.
Fifth day, drain same and add 2 cups sugar.
Bring to boil and pour over pickles.
Sixth day, drain and reheat liquid and add 1 cup sugar.
Return liquid to pickles.
Seventh day, drain and pack pickles in jars.
Reheat syrup and 1 cup mor sugar.
Pour boiling liquid over pickles in jars.
Clean tops of jars and seal with lids.

title: super lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to package instructions.
Drain.
Brown beef in large skillet in oil with onions and garlic.
Add tomato paste and sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt, oregano, bay leaf, basil, parsley, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1/2 cup of water; simmer for 1 hour.
Combine cottage cheese, egg, remaining salt and remaining pepper.
Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Arrange layers of noodles, cottage cheese mixture, beef mixture and cheese in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; let set for 15 minutes before serving. This recipe will serve 7 people.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, grapes, celery and walnuts in a medium-size bowl.
Pour on Honey-Yogurt Dressing.
Stir gently to mix well. Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Add more mayonnaise if not smooth enough.
Season with a little salt and pepper.
Store in covered container.

title: reuben jr.
directions: Rinse and drain sauerkraut, mix
with salad dressing.
Scrape fat from corned beef.
Mash meat well.
Cut Swiss cheese slices in quarters.
Blend butter and mustard and spread on bread.
Top with 1 tablespoon sauerkraut, then 1 tablespoon beef.
Add a square of cheese on top each slice.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 8 minutes.

title: baked cheese casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 8 slices of bread on bottom of pan.
Lay slice of ham and cheese on each slice of bread.
Mix together the milk, mustard, half and half or evaporated milk, salt and eggs.
Pour over the ham and cheese in pan.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight (or 6 to 8 hours). Before baking, sprinkle with 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted margarine or butter.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Test casserole for doneness by inserting knife in center. Casserole should be served as soon as possible.

title: belgian meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour, fat and tomatoes.
Make balls; roll in flour and brown in heavy pot.
Add tomatoes; cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken-stuffing bake
directions: In 1-quart saucepan over high heat, heat 3/4 cup of the milk and butter to scalding.
In large bowl, pour hot milk mixture over stuffing; toss to mix well.
Put 1/2 of the stuffing mixture into buttered 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Mix together with dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and chips.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheets.
Press with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour and add milk and chocolate.
Add well beaten eggs and cook in a double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Use egg whites for meringue.
You can also use this mixture for a chocolate pudding, too.

title: caramel breakfast roll
directions: Thaw bread in refrigerator overnight.
Quarter loaf, cut each quarter in 8 cubes so that you have 32 cubes.
Combine dry pudding mix, sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Dip each cube in melted butter then roll in pudding mix.
Put in a 6-cup ring mold in 3 layers. Drizzle with remaining butter and sprinkle with pudding mix. Cover and let rise in warm place until double (1 to 1 1/2 hours). Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meaty spanish rice pie
directions: Measure Product 19; crush to 1/2 cup.
In a large mixing bowl, combine crushed cereal, milk, onion and salt; add ground beef. Mix only until combined.
Press mixture evenly around sides in a 9-inch pie pan to form meat in pie shell.
Set aside the pie shell.

title: hot sweet pickles
directions: Cut sour pickles and jalapenos crosswise into rounds (seeding jalapenos is optional).
Peel garlic, leaving cloves whole.
Heat vinegar, sugar and oil to just below boiling.
Pour over pickles, jalapenos and garlic in a large bowl.
Marinate in refrigerator for five days, stirring occasionally.
Put into smaller jars and keep refrigerated.

title: german cabbage rolls
directions: Submerge cabbage in boiling water until they can be separated. Cool to handle.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans on pizza pan or platter.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and spread on top of beans.
Spread lettuce over sour cream. Sprinkle on onions, then cheese. Top with tomatoes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Roll chopped nuts, orange slice candy and dates in 1/2 cup of the flour.
Sift the remaining 3 cups flour with the soda and salt.
Cream butter and buttermilk together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sugar and next the 3 remaining cups of flour.
Mix well.
Add coconut to cake batter.
Blend well.
Add nuts, orange slice candy and dates.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Toss orange slices, dates and pecans in the 1/2 cup of reserved flour.
Cream sugar and butter, add one egg at a time beating after adding each egg.
Mix soda in buttermilk and add flour and buttermilk alternately to sugar mixture.
Add
coconut, candy and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. This is better after it has been frozen.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and sliver chicken breast halves. Reserve broth.
Layer mushroom soup, broth, curry powder and lemon juice.
Cover with mayonnaise.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: german sweet chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in 2-quart saucepan over very low heat.
Stir constantly until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 3/4 cup sugar until well blended.
Add 2 eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in 1/2 cup flour and nuts (optional) until well mixed. Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Mix the cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 egg and 1 tablespoon flour in same pan until smooth. Spoon over brownie mixture. Swirl with knife to marbleize.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Do not overbake!
Makes 16.

title: hard rock candy
directions: You will need an aluminum oven liner.

title: double corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until firm to touch. Can be reheated and is just as good left over.

title: onion bread
directions: Cut loaf lengthwise.
Mix scallions and butter; spread on loaf.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese bread
directions: Butter 9 x 5-inch pan.
Separate biscuits.
Stand on edge in 2 rows side to side.
Sprinkle grated cheese between layers and on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm.

title: easy packet meals
directions: On a foil square, place a pat of butter, meat patty and slices of onion, potato and carrot.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fold over foil and seal.
Place on charcoal grill or open fire for half an hour, turning after first 15 minutes.
Cooking time depends on heat of fire.
Make one packet per person.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Scald together the first 4 ingredients, then stir in the cornstarch and milk.
Mix and cook for 5 minutes more.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold with fruit, if desired.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: In baking dish, layer chips.
Mix chicken and soup; put on top of chips.
Layer tomatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut sweet potatoes into 1 x 2-inch chunks.
Boil sweet potatoes 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sugar, brown sugar and margarine.
Sprinkle cinnamon to taste.
Cook on stove for 30 minutes to 45 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in frying pan.
Add onion and cook over low heat until lightly brown.
Mix bread crumbs, water and cream and let stand a few minutes.
Add ground beef and pork, salt, pepper, sugar and onion until thoroughly mixed.
Shape into very small meatballs.
Melt remaining butter in pan.
Add meatballs and brown slowly.
Allow about 25 minutes for browning. Shake pan occasionally to brown evenly.
Yield:
About 48 tiny meatballs.

title: lucy's special
directions: Marinate steak,
cut into bite size pieces, for as long as possible
in
enough
Italian
dressing
to cover.	Prepare spaghetti or
preferred
pasta;
set
aside.
Saute
meat with onion until meat is cooked through and onion is tender.
Serve over pasta or rice.
Additional dressing can be added if pasta is not fully coated with dressing from meat mixture.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: micro-fudge
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla until partially mixed.
Mixture will be stiff.
Put butter on top but do not mix.
Microwave on High for two minutes or until milk feels warm on bottom of bowl.
Stir vigorously until smooth. Mix in nuts. Pour into 8 x 4 x 3-inch dish.
Chill 1 hour.

title: south of the border bundles
directions: Brown ground meat and set aside. In medium saucepan, combine salsa and cheese; cook over medium heat until cheese melts. Set aside 1 1/4 c. of mixture. Add meat to remaining mixture in sauce pan. Spoon mixture into tortillas; roll tortillas and place (seam side down) in a greased baking dish. Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Pour sauce, that was set aside, over bundles. Serve and enjoy!

title: peach crunch
directions: Spoon peaches into an 8-inch dish.
Top with Oat Topping. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable rice
directions: Wash and soak rice at least 15 minutes.
Plunge carrots, beans and cauliflower in boiling water and blanch for 3 minutes.
Drain and keep aside.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix in this order:
peas, soup, sugar, pepper, pimento and almonds.
Heat from the peas will be enough to warm the other ingredients.
Mix well and serve.
Serves 12.

title: baked beans
directions: In large frying pan, put bacon and fry until it almost burned. Take out and put on paper towel.
Put the 2 cut-up onions in the bacon grease and cook until brown.
Add the beans, brown sugar and molasses.
Mix well.
Turn fire down to simmer.
Add bacon, crumble it on top.
Simmer for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: gayle's garlic bread
directions: Heat butter, garlic and salt until melted and flavors well blended.
Slice loaves in half, lengthwise, making top and bottom pieces.
Then cut into 1-inch slices through both halves. Saturate bread completely with this mixture.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, uncover and place in preheated 350° to 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn off heat and leave bread in oven until it is served (not too long).
Bread must be hot and cooked this long to be good.
Should be crusty.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Stir all ingredients (except raisins) with fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously 1 minute.
Stir in raisins.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all but last two ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
If desired, serve over chow mein noodles. If desired, use 10 fresh mushrooms and 2 tablespoons bell pepper.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Peel pears and drop in salt water.
Take a spoon and spoon out core part.
Boil in mixture of 2 parts water and 1 part sugar. Cook fast until tender.
Pack in jars; fill with hot syrup and seal.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour and flavoring; beat well.
Bake for 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: jam bites
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Stir in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
(If dough is soft, cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.) Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough into 12 equal parts.
Shape each part into strip, 8 x 1 1/2-inches, on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make indentation lengthwise down center of each strip with handle of wooden spoon.
Spread 1 teaspoon jam in each.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes; cut strips at an angle into 1-inch slices.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: borscht(makes 10 servings)
directions: Saute
onions
in butter 15 minutes.
Add
cabbage
and beets; mix with stock and let boil for 15 minutes.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, garlic and green peppers.
Boil
slowly 15 to 20 minutes.
Add beet juice, lemon, sugar and vinegar.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Serve with sour cream.
Serve hot or cold.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a shaker jar or with an electric mixer on low speed.
Dressing is great on tossed salad. Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: dilly green beans
directions: Boil beans, water, and salt uncovered for 5 minutes.
Plunge into cold water and drain.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil. Pour over beans.
Cool and cover.
Refrigerate.

title: pizza pan breakfast
directions: Press crescent rolls flat onto a 14-inch pizza pan, forming crust.
Brown and drain sausage.
Crumble and sprinkle on crescent crust.
Sprinkle hash browns and cheese over meat.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together; pour over pizza.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Mix together candy and nuts separate.
Break up 1/2 of angel food cake into 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 candy/nut mixture, followed by 1/2 Cool Whip mixture.
Repeat and top with remaining candy.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: microwave cherry crunch
directions: Place butter in small bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 1 minute.
Stir in oats and brown sugar; microwave, uncovered, at High for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour and cinnamon.
Place pie filling in 1-quart casserole.
Stir in almond extract.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over filling.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 5 minutes.
Spoon into dessert dishes and top with vanilla ice cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.
Quick and easy.

title: stuffed squid(calamari ripieni el forno)
directions: Clean
squid but leave whole.
Remove tentacles and set aside. Skin
body of squid and remove head and insides.
Soak in
salt water
and then rinse.
Drain, wash and rinse again. In mixing bowl add eggs, breadcrumbs, 1 clove of the garlic, 2 tablespoons parsley,
pepper
and Parmesan cheese together to make a thick paste.
If too thin, add a little more cheese.

title: mabel's salmagundi bake
directions: In greased casserole layer rice; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour over 1 can only tomato sauce and the hot water.
Add a layer of onion and green pepper, then beef.
Sprinkle with salt. Top with a layer of corn.
Add chili powder to other can of tomato sauce and pour over.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour, then uncovered for 15 minutes at 375°.
Serves 12.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients in baking dish. Bake at 375° about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Top with grated cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese is golden brown.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain.
Combine macaroni and remaining ingredients; toss gently to mix.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Serve cold.
Serving amount is 3/4 cup with 83 calories.

title: cream puffs and filling
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bring water, butter and salt to boil.
Add flour all at once, then beat over low heat until mixture leaves side of pan and forms compact ball.
Remove from heat; continue beating to cool mixture (2 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until mixture has satin-like sheen.
Onto greased baking sheet, drop 5 or 6 mounds about 2 inches apart.
Bake until well browned and puffy, about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; immediately cut 1 or 2 slits in each side of puff; return to oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: scrambled dogs
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs together with salt and pepper.
Pour into greased frying pan.
Add sliced wieners.
Add cheese, mixing all ingredients together.
Cook until eggs are scrambled.

title: shirley fromm's tangerine marmalade(double recipe)
directions: You will need jelly jars, sterilized and hot.

title: cocoa krispie treats
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter together in large saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth. Remove from heat.
Add Cocoa Krispies.
Stir until well coated. Press mixture evenly into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Remove from refrigerator 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: shell salad
directions: Cook
macaroni	as
directed.
Add
vegetables (cut and diced as	desired).
Mix with salt and mayonnaise like potato salad. Chill and serve.

title: bob's blobs
directions: Mix ingredients together and bring to boil over medium heat. Boil 1 minute.
Drop by spoonfuls from high elevation onto wax paper.
Cool and eat.

title: korean barbeque & sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Marinate beef squares, short ribs or chicken 4 to 5 hours in covered dish in refrigerator.
Charcoal broil.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Sift flour, baking powder, and salt. Stir into butter mixture, alternately with the milk.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon butter into greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Spoon mashed peaches (3 to 4 cups) over batter.
Sprinkle with 1/4 c. sugar.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350 degree oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, carrots, olives, pimiento and onion.
Add eggs and seasonings.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add flour, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard.
Mix well.
Add tomatoes and cubed bread. Save enough bread crumbs to put on top.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks, stir in sweetened condensed milk and lemon.
Pour into crust.

title: oatmeal-raisin crispies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix in soda, salt and flour. Mix in rolled oats and raisins.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto baking sheet, leaving room for cookies to spread.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: whaky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in pan.
Make 3 holes in dry mixture.
Put 6 tablespoons oil in one hole, 1 teaspoon vanilla in another hole and 1 tablespoon vinegar in other hole.
Pour 1 cup cold water over all; stir with fork until smooth.

title: cranberry ice
directions: Boil cranberries with water until tender. Strain. Boil sugar and quart of water for 5 minutes. Add sugar water, juice of lemons, and gelatin which has been softened in cold water, to the cranberries. Freeze, stirring several times during freezing. Remove from freezer 10-15 minutes before serving.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until smooth.
Stir in milk until frosting reaches spreading consistency.

title: melanie frazier's easy popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows on High 2 minutes.
Stir to combine.
Microwave 1 minute longer and stir until smooth.
(Tint with food coloring, if desired.)
Gradually mix in popped corn until well coated.
Grease hands and form balls.
(Use same recipe for Rice Krispie treats, using 6 cups cereal.)

title: pace picante chicken
directions: Combine picante sauce, mustard, brown sugar and salt.
Pour over chicken breast in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: ritzy pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder until stiff.
Add sugar. Fold in Ritz, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool at least 30 minutes and spread with Cool Whip. (Note:
This doesn't go in a pie crust, just pour directly in pie pan).

title: whiskey sour slush
directions: Mix in blender.
Add ice cubes and crush in blender.
Serves 4 glasses.

title: spice nut cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour two (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round baking pans.
In a mixer bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients.
Add shortening, brown sugar and buttermilk or sour milk, mixing until all the flour is moistened.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes more.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes on wire racks.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: salmon spread
directions: Place salmon in strainer; drain thoroughly (only if using canned salmon).
Flake salmon with fork.
Combine all ingredients; mix until smooth.
Chill overnight before using.
Spread on toast points or fill rosette cups.

title: company potato casserole
directions: Place sliced potatoes in a casserole dish. Top with butter, onion soup and water. Stir in all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned vegetable soup(makes 12 cups)
directions: In large heavy pan, over medium-high heat, brown beef in margarine.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in beef broth, water and celery; heat to a boil.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.
Add tomatoes, peas and carrots, potatoes and steak sauce, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes more until potatoes are done.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Place sugar, vinegar and oil in saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil and let cool.
Pour over kraut mixture; stir well.
Store in refrigerator.
Ready to eat, and it's really good.

title: southern eggnog
directions: Separate white from yolk.
Beat white until stiff.
Add half of sugar to white and continue to beat until sugar is dissolved and white stands in peaks.
At the same time, beat yolk with other half of sugar.
The yolk should become lighter in color.
Add whiskey slowly while beating.
I like electric mixer better than a blender for beating.
The yolk should then become thicker as whiskey "cooks" the yolk.
No milk is added.
Fold stiff white into the yolk.
The mixture will be very stiff.
Serve in glass; eat with spoon.
Some prefer to add whipped cream, but I think it makes it too rich.
If preferred, sprinkle with freshly grated nutmeg. Serve with pound cake.
Scrumptious!

title: iroquois ghost bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Make well in center.
Add milk slowly, mixing to biscuit consistency.
Knead a few times on floured board until mixture sticks together.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and slash opening in center (or cut with cutter for individual servings).
Heat oil in heavy skillet (hot, but not smoking) 1/4 to 1/2-inch deep.
Cook dough until brown on underside.
Turn and brown other side.
Drain on paper towels. Serve warm or hot.
Split and spread with butter, jam, honey or maple syrup.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container. Cook chicken over a hot fire. Apply sauce often with a brush and turn chicken often. Be sure sauce is stirred well before applying to chicken each time. Chicken is done when leg twists off.
(Will do 50 chicken halves.)

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning until smooth. Chop onions, tomatoes and lettuce.
Keep separate.
On a large plate or tray, spread out mix.
Layer onions first, then tomatoes, then lettuce.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Refrigerate to chill sauce and toppings.
Serve with nachos or Doritos.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Press to sides of mini-muffin pan.

title: cheese-pecan ball
directions: Mix cheeses and onion by hand.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix again.
Refrigerate several hours.
Shape into ball.
Roll in parsley and nuts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
May be frozen.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, onion and bread together.
Form into medium size balls and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Drain pineapple chunks and reserve liquid.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water, then fill rest of cup with water.

title: brown rice and spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach per package directions and drain off excess moisture.
Mix hot spinach, rice and cheese in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish and mix until cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 to 40 minutes until bubbling and brown on top.
May sprinkle extra cheese on top according to desire.
May adjust rice and spinach according to taste.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips 3 minutes on High in microwave oven in a Corning Ware bowl with a glass lid.
Mix all ingredients and spoon onto wax paper or foil.

title: potatoes and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with corn flakes.
Grease large casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: sherbet salad
directions: Take the jello, boiling water and orange sherbet; mix and chill.
When partly set, add mandarin oranges, pineapple and bananas.
Chill.
Keeps well.

title: plain roll dough
directions: Soften active yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup of flour; beat well.
Beat in softened yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form a soft dough, beating well.
Cover and let rise in warm place (82°) until doubled (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Make into rolls or cinnamon rolls.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix flour with the softened cream cheese and butter.
Pinch a piece of dough off and make 1-inch ball and put into a very small muffin tin.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Combine all marinade ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Place chicken in an 11 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cook very slowly at 300° until chicken is cooked, approximately 45 to 60 minutes.
Excellent appetizer.

title: no bake peanut butter balls
directions: In small bowl, mix milk, peanut butter, honey and graham crackers until blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in coating. Makes 24.

title: dip for apple slices
directions: Combine cream cheese and brown sugar. Let stand 15 minutes. Add sugar and vanilla. Add crushed peanuts. Serve with apple slices.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, condensed milk and juice from lemons.
Mix well.
Pour in crust; cover with beaten egg whites.
Bake until brown.
Keep in refrigerator until set, about 2 hours.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Melt candy bar and wax slowly in double boiler, stirring constantly. Hold whole berry by the stem and dip it in slightly cooled chocolate. Let dry on wax paper. Place in refrigerator about 1 minute to harden.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Combine chicken, onion, soup and jalapeno cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer tortillas, chicken and cheese mixture.
Top with Cheddar and Swiss cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with olives (optional).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix with ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Pour into a greased 2-quart dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool, about 15 minutes, and serve.

title: shrimp pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine shrimp, snow peas, tomatoes, parsley, orange zest, oil, pasta, salt and pepper.
Toss together well. Before serving, add orange juice and toss.
Serves 6.

title: poor man's spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Melt oleo in skillet. Saute ham until lightly browned.
Dice. (Or cook bacon, crumble or chop into pieces.)
Drain spaghetti well. Return to pot.
Immediately add the ham (or bacon), eggs, cream, chives, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Toss lightly.
(Heat from the spaghetti cooks the eggs.)
Add cheese and toss lightly again. Enjoy!

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Put butter and peanut butter in pan and heat to mix.
When mixed, pour over warm popcorn and mix until all popcorn is covered.
Serve immediately.

title: japanese chicken wings
directions: Roll wings in cornstarch, then beaten egg.
Fry in at least 1/2 inch of oil.
Place in baking dish.
Mix all sauce ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook until bouillon cube dissolves.
Pour over wings.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, in 350° oven.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat undiluted soup to a boil.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/3 cup cold water.
Add gelatine mixture to soup.
Add mayo to softened cream cheese.
Add cream cheese mixture to tomato mixture.
Cool. Add onion, celery, shrimp and lemon juice.
Pour into serving bowl.
Chill at least 8 hours or until set.
Serve as spread for crackers.

title: crabbies
directions: Combine crab meat, butter, Cheez Whiz, garlic powder and mayonnaise in a bowl.
Mix well. Spread on English muffins. Place on baking sheet. Broil 4-inches from heat until brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and green pepper together.
Boil macaroni just to tender and drain.
Mix together meat, macaroni and all other ingredients.
Bake in covered casserole at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Use cheese on top layers.

title: super sandwiches
directions: Spread 2 slices with mayonnaise or salad dressing. Layer each slice of bread with 1 slice cheese, half of the apple slices and another slice of cheese.
Top with another slice of bread. Spread each outside with margarine or butter and grill 6 to 8 minutes and cheese is melted.
Makes 2 servings.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Spray a cookie sheet with rimmed edge with cooking spray. Lay graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Melt butter and add brown sugar. Cook for 2 minutes.
Spread mixture on top of graham crackers. Sprinkle pecan pieces on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and take off cookie sheet.
Break into pieces and store in a closed container.

title: loaded mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and place in mixing bowl. Add sour cream, milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat on medium-low speed until light and fluffy.
Stir in 2 cups cheese, bacon and onions.
Transfer to a greased 3-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake,
uncovered,
at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.
Serves 14.

title: chili cheese appetizers
directions: Lay green chili on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle
cheese on chili.	Pour eggs over cheese and sprinkle paprika
on
top for color.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cut into
inch
squares and serve warm with large tortilla chips.

title: s'mores(for the chocolate lover)
directions: Microwave Method:
Break graham crackers in half.
Break chocolate bar into 4 sections.
Center one section on each of 4 graham cracker halves.
Top each with marshmallow.
Place on paper towel.
Microwave at High (100%) for 10 to 15 seconds or until marshmallow puffs.
Top each with another graham cracker half; press gently.
Let stand 1 minute to soften chocolate.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 snacks.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together; stir well.
Pour into greased baking dish; bake at 450° for 1 hour.
Take from oven.
Stir about every 15 minutes while cooking.

title: st. patrick's day pie
directions: In medium bowl, whisk together pudding mix and evaporated milk.
Stir in 1 cup whipped topping.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: gregory's goulash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Brown onion.
Boil and drain noodles.
In a large pot, mix soup, corn, beans, beef, onion, water and noodles.
Heat until hot and thickened.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Some old-fashioned recipes tickle the fancy.

title: beef rolls in beer
directions: In bowl, combine sausage, onion and crumbs.
Shape into 8 cylinders.
Salt and pepper steak.
Place each cylinder on slice of steak.
Roll up to enclose filling.
Wrap each roll in bacon; secure with toothpicks.
Brown over low heat.
Slowly add beer and 4 or 5 beef bouillon cubes.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add mushrooms and juice any time.
Thicken gravy.
Delicious for company meal.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, margarine, milk, vanilla and egg; blend well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Add flour, baking powder and salt that have been sifted; mix well. Cover with plastic wrap and chill at least 1 hour for easier handling.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Prepare noodle rings according to package.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Drain pineapple into large bowl.
Whisk pudding mix into pineapple juice.
Add Cool Whip.
Whisk again.
Add all noodles, pineapple, drained oranges and marshmallows; blend.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake according to package.
Now grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in cake.
Mix Ricotta, sugar, vanilla and eggs together.
Pour this mixture on top of cake.
Spread evenly on top.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo and mix with pretzels.
Pat into 9 x 12-inch baking pan and bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool completely and sprinkle nuts on top.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sweetener.
Smooth over pretzel crust.
Mix Jell-O, 2 cups water and strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate until set.

title: red cabbage with diced apples
directions: Combine all ingredients except water and Sweet 'N Low in large saucepan.
Add water.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.
Stir in Sweet 'N Low.

title: john wayne beans
directions: Cook bacon until almost done.
Add pepper and onion.
Cook until soft.
Add ground hamburger.
Cook until done.
Add green chilies, stewed tomatoes, soup and beans.
Just before serving, stir in 1/2 pound grated Velveeta cheese.
Add sausage when you add the cooked beans.
Cook all ingredients for about 15 minutes in a large heavy pan.
Sausage should be cut into 1-inch long pieces.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add cooked pumpkin, milk, eggs and butter.
Mix spices with flour and sugar.
Cook on medium on stove top until slightly thick.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix well the Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Put in shells.
Top with coconut.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in 1 3/4 cups water.
Mix avocado, parsley flakes, onions, soup, cheese and rice.
Spray casserole dish with Pam. Add mixture.
Sprinkle top of casserole with Millet Cheese, then add crushed cracker crumbs on top of Millet Cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan brown sugar cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, eggs, vanilla extract and brown sugar. Mix on a low speed. (Very important to mix on low speed to prevent cake from turning into a quiche.)
Mix about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: sliced marinated lamb
directions: Place lamb in large plastic food bag.
Combine garlic, onion, lemon juice, olive oil, oregano and rosemary in bowl and add to meat.
Close bag next to meat.
Working through bag, distribute marinade over meat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bring to room temperature before cooking.
Remove lamb from marinade, reserving marinade.
Season meat to taste with salt and pepper.
Broil or grill lamb on both sides until done as desired.
Place on warm platter and tent with foil.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and cream cheese. Add eggs one at a time, then slowly add flour and vanilla. Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Do not open oven until done.

title: amish garlic sweet dills
directions: Heat to boiling sugar, vinegar, water and salt.
Pour into jars with cucumbers and tighten lids.
Process water bath 8 to 10 minutes.
Ready to eat after 2 weeks.
Use medium cucumbers sliced 1/4-inch thick and place into jars.
Place 1 garlic bud and 1 to 2 sprigs of fresh green dill to each quart.

title: fumi salad
directions: Brown nuts and sesame seed in a skillet until lightly browned. Crush noodles in your hands.
When nuts and seeds have cooled, add them to noodles.
Keep all dry ingredients together.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Roll into balls and then into mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake until brown but soft at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Dip in melted margarine; coat chicken with flour.
Put in baking pan lined with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: corn balls
directions: Cook celery in butter until tender.
Add corn and water and bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over stuffing.
Mix lightly.
Stir in eggs and seasonings.
Shape into 12 balls.
Place in 8 cup casserole dish and pour 1/4 cup melted butter over balls.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Mix cake mix and jello. Add eggs, oil and wine. Beat with mixer on low speed until moistened, then beat on medium speed 3 minutes. Grease and flour a Bundt cake pan. Sprinkle pecans in bottom, then pour in batter. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions. Drain and add margarine and milk and stir until dissolved. Add 2 cans of cheese soup and stir well. Add can of crushed tomatoes (mix well). Top with bread crumbs, then cover with American cheese slices. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Cook bacon partially.
Slit weenies from end to end (not all the way through).
Put one to two slices of cheese into slit. Wrap partially cooked bacon around the weenies; use toothpicks to hold the bacon in place.
Put in broiler until cheese melts.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook the squash and onion together in water until tender. Drain and add sour cream, soup and grated carrots.
Combine the dressing mix with the melted butter. Put half the dressing in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the vegetables and top with the remaining dressing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: snowball cake
directions: Break the cake in bite-size pieces.
Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Add boiling water, pineapple, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until partly congealed.
Fold in 1 container of Cool Whip.
Stir in angel food cake.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle coconut on top.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate fried pies
directions: Mix your favorite pie crust, roll out thin and cut in 6-inch circle.
Place cocoa and sugar mixture (about 1 tablespoon of mixture), 1 pat of butter and a drop or two of vanilla into circle. Fold over and pinch edge together.
Cook in Crisco until brown on each side over low heat.

title: special k bars
directions: Boil Karo syrup and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Add 3 cups or more Special K cereal. Put into buttered pan.
Pack down.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top of bars.

title: moszetti
directions: Brown ground beef in cooking oil and drain.
Then, cook green pepper, onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add soup and seasonings.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a large baking dish (sprayed with Pam).
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: russian potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a deep glass casserole, layer potatoes, butter, onions, "globs" of sour cream, salt, pepper, potatoes, onions etc.
For the top, seal the whole area with a heavy layer of sour cream, making sure there are no cracks in the sour cream.
Bake in the oven for 30 to 45 minutes until everything is "bubbling" and the edges of the top layer become slightly brown.
Sprinkle top with paprika and serve hot.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash and cut okra in chunks.
Soak in cold milk about 15 minutes.
Put flour in bag and drop okra in; shake it until covered.
Put in hot grease until brown.
Will stay crisp all day.

title: apple custard
directions: Mix ingredients well; pour into pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 320°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla, in 3-quart saucepan. Beat 1 minute.
Place over medium-low heat or in double boiler and beat constantly until peaks form (7 minutes).
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and beat to consistency for spreading.

title: berry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fit bottom crust into 8-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Cover with berries.
Mix sugar, tapioca and all of the berries.
Drizzle lemon juice over mixture and dot with butter. Top with crust; seal and flute edges.
Sprinkle top crust with remaining tablespoon of sugar.
Cut steam vents.

title: cold trout
directions: Place wine, water, tarragon and parsley in a pan big enough for the trout.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Gently place trout in the simmering liquid and cook over a low fire for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Remove skeleton, chop into bite-size pieces, enjoy.

title: my favorite cookie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar together and add rest of ingredients except chocolate chips. Mix well then add chocolate chips, 8oz grated Hershey bar and 3 c. chopped nuts (any kind). Make golf ball size cookies and place 2 in. apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 min.
Yield 112 cookies.

title: broccoli rice dish
directions: Cook rice.
Rinse frozen broccoli in cold water to separate. Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crispy walnut chicken
directions: Process cereal and walnuts until crumbs are fine.
Combine butter, a dash of garlic powder, salt and pepper; stir well. Dredge chicken in butter mixture, then in cereal mixture.
Arrange chicken in jelly roll pan.
Pour any remaining butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mushroom herb casserole
directions: Wash mushrooms lightly.
Put in shallow casserole.
Add marjoram, salt and chives to butter.
Pour over mushrooms.
Mix chicken broth and cream.
Pour into casserole.
Cover and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Remove cover last 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: potato salad(german kartoffel-salat)
directions: Cook potatoes; peel
and
slice
medium thick.	Combine with onion, dill, and
parsley.	Season	with salt and pepper. Add cut up eggs
(optional).
Heat	oil,
vinegar
and
