sugar. Pour over potato mixture.
Add
garnish of cucumber slices and pickled herring if desired.

title: blue ribbon crescent rolls
directions: Scald milk in saucepan.
Combine milk, oil, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add beaten eggs.
Add flour and mix until smooth and soft dough.
Knead dough lightly on floured surface.
Place in lightly greased bowl and lid; cover.
Place in draft-free place; let rise until double in bulk, then divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll into the circles (about size of a pie crust).
Spread with melted butter with pastry brush.
Cut circles into triangles (like pieces of pie). Roll, starting at wide end to the point.
Place on greased cookie sheet with point underneath.
Let rise again until light and fluffy.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
After baking use pastry brush and brush tops and sides with melted butter.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti, then layer spaghetti, followed by spaghetti sauce in casserole dish.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream and layer over spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top and bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix and melt (over very low heat) chips, marshmallows, milk and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Cool completely.
Then fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Chill.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Soften ice cream just enough to blend.
Mix pudding and milk in separate bowl.
Blend into softened ice cream.
Fold in 4 ounces of Cool Whip.
Put mixture on baked cracker bottom.
Bake crumbs for topping in separate pan at 375° for 3 to 4 minutes.
Garnish with remaining topping crumbs.
Freeze, but refrigerate 1/2 hour or longer before serving.

title: bisquick zucchini snack
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an oblong pan (9 x 13-inch). Mix all ingredients together; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: freida's pickles
directions: Add cucumbers, onions, peppers, garlic and cloves in a large bowl.
Add salt; cover with cracked ice, then mix thoroughly and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain completely; place ingredients in large cooking pot.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumber mix.
Heat to boiling and seal in sterilized hot jars or cool mixture and store in refrigerator.
Add vinegar and sugar, if needed to cover pickles before heating.

title: quick and easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, debone and remove skin.
Cut chicken into small pieces.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Cream peanut butter and margarine in double boiler over hot water until melted.
Add sugar, egg and flour; mix well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 350°, about 10 minutes or until brown on bottom.

title: low cholesterol spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Let simmer for 20 minutes. Then spoon over cooked pasta.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain well.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine all other ingredients in crock-pot.
Add onion.
Cook until hot.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine the cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts. In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour half of batter into Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix the cornbread mix as per the packaging and bake. Cut up squash in cubes and steam in water to cook. Add salt and pepper to the squash while lightly steaming. Drain. In a large bowl, crumble the cornbread, then add cooked squash and mix. Continue to add diced onion, butter (melted), soup and water. Mix thoroughly and add seasoning to taste. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serve with fried chicken and green beans.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute green peppers and onions in margarine. Combine with remaining ingredients, except cheese. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with cheese. Bake 45 to 55 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: hot crab triangles
directions: Beat softened cheese until fluffy.
Combine mustard with milk and add to cheese.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spread generously on bread slices.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika. Cut each slice into 4 triangles and put on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until well browned.
Makes 48.

title: rich vanilla ice cream
directions: Separate eggs; beat whites until stiff.
Add sugar, cream, half and half, vanilla, Eagle Brand and egg yolks.
Add enough milk to fill churn to fill line.
Churn according to directions. Makes 5 quarts.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook (boil) chicken and remove meat.
Cook celery and onion in butter.
Mix soup with one can of water each (2 cans).
Place rice in casserole pan and mix in chicken, peas, onions, rice and soup. Mix in sage, salt and pepper.
Bake for 1/2 hour with buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325°.

title: sunflower-alfalfa-yogurt slaw
directions: In a large bowl, mix well yogurt, parsley, chives, sugar, lemon peel and juice.
Add cabbage, sprouts and sunflower seeds; toss to mix well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Add baking powder and salt to flour and sift 4 times.
Beat egg yolks, add water to egg yolks and beat until light.
Sift sugar and measure.
Add to egg mixture and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Add flour to egg mixture and beat until thoroughly blended.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff but not dry.
Fold beaten egg whites into batter.
Bake in ungreased tube pan in 325° oven about 1 hour. When cake is thoroughly cool, cut in 3 layers.
Place filling in between layers and top of cake.

title: chocolate chip biscotti(makes 12 biscuits)
directions: Beat butter with mixer.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Mix in vanilla and orange rind.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt in another bowl.
Stir into butter mixture. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Dough will be firm.
Shape dough into log, 12-inches long, 2-inches wide and 3/4-inch high.
Place on greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and reduce to 300°.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into 12 (1-inch) slices and place each slice on its side on baking sheet. Toast biscotti 15 minutes on each side until golden.

title: cheese casserole bread
directions: Combine flours, baking powder, onion, salt, sugar substitute and Italian herb seasoning in a medium bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine milk, margarine and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Separate broccoli into bite size pieces in a large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and pour them over broccoli. Marinate overnight in refrigerator, turning broccoli in marinade a couple of times.
Drain and serve on platter as hors d'oeuvres.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with brown sugar and melted oleo. Place in round cake pan. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar. Cut in shortening. Add milk and mix well. Spoon over peaches. Bake on top rack of oven for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: This is not lo-cal or low-fat, but good!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in a small amount of boiling, salted water until slightly tender; drain.
Cook carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini or put in layer.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: pineapple-cherry cake frosting
directions: Cook all ingredients together until thick enough to spread.

title: cinnamon raisin bread
directions: Combine milk and 1/4 cup butter, stirring until butter melts. Cool mixture to 105° to 115°.
Combine 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup plus 1 tablespoon sugar, salt and yeast.
Gradually add milk mixture to dry ingredients, mixing at low speed of electric mixer.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 3/4 cup flour; beat at medium-high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough (2 1/2 to 3 cups); stir in raisins.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 7 minutes).

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs, yogurt and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients that have been mixed together.
Do not overstir!

title: butterscotch maple cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light. Beat in egg. Sift flour with salt, soda and cinnamon. Stir into butter mixture until mixture forms a ball. Divide dough into 3 parts. Shape each on waxed paper in a roll about 2-inches in diameter. Chill until firm.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices. Put on greased cookie sheets. Brush with maple syrup. Place almond half on each cookie. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Layer fruit in serving bowl.
Pour orange juice over fruit and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Place in bottom of deep dish pie plate (glass).
Spread can of chili on top of mixture.
Thinly slice cheese and place over chili.
Microwave mixture until cheese melts (approximately 4 to 5 minutes).
Dip in your favorite nachos and enjoy!

title: mocha cream almondine
directions: In small saucepan, combine milk, heavy cream, coffee and cocoa. Heat.
Stir until coffee dissolves. Remove from heat.
Add almond liqueur. Pour into heat proof mugs.
Garnish with whipped cream and sliced almonds.
Serves 2.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Put butter in bottom of small can.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Add pineapple.
Cover with cake mix.
Fill can 1/2 full.
Cover can with foil and put in fire for 15 minutes.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt, syrup, vanilla and butter well.
Spread pecans in unbaked pie shell and pour mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cook onion, celery and carrot until tender.
Add all ingredients together.

title: homemade face paint
directions: I have a little recipe that isn't hard to make.
But you must always start as you awake.
Take a great big mixing bowl.
Fill it with a smile.
Mix half a cup of sunshine with good deeds all the while.
Add a pinch of work and play, a pinch of thoughtfulness and care, but don't bake it in the oven, just spread it everywhere!

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat again.
Add margarine and then vanilla.
Add flour and beat well.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until browned.
Cool 5 minutes.
Invert on plate.
Serve warm or cold.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of broccoli soup

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra, leaving stems on.
Pack in clean jars tightly.
Mix ingredients for brine and bring to a boil. Pour over packed okra and seal tightly.
Process in hot bath for 5 minutes.
Small onions may be used like this also.

title: fat-free tortilla soup(caldo tlapeno from cancun, mexico)
directions: Bring the water and bouillon cubes to a boil.
Peel and cube the first 5 vegetables and add to the broth.
Dice the garlic and add it along with bay leaves, 1/2 to 1 teaspoon red pepper and the cumin seed.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: sausage pie
directions: Skin and saute sausage; drain.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Break up sausage and crumble in bottom of pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Mix other ingredients (except grated cheese and paprika).
Pour over Mozzarella and sausage.
Sprinkle grated cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Loosen around sides.
Cut in desired sizes when cool.
For appetizer.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet and drain.
Put in a casserole dish.
Make enough mashed potatoes to cover ground beef. Sprinkle cheese on top and put in oven long enough to melt cheese; serve hot.

title: pilaf stuffed chicken
directions: Fry onion in 1/4 cup of butter in saucepan until transparent. Add pine nuts and rice; saute until light brown.
Add currants, water and dash of pepper.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until the water is absorbed.
Add melted butter.
Cool before using as stuffing.
Stuff chicken with 1 cup of pilaf.
Combine yogurt and salt; brush half over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 1 hour more, basting with yogurt.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add remaining ingredients, except pecans. Mix together.
Chill and roll into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients with hand, then roll out on floured board.
Roll thin and cut into about 1-inch squares and drop in hot chicken broth.

title: joey morrison's fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together in a large bowl with juices.
Chill before serving.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning envelope with the sour cream.
On platter, spread refried beans, then the sour cream mixture.
Continue making layers with the rest of the ingredients in the order they are listed.
Serve with taco chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill until ready to serve.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into pan layered with vanilla wafers. Sprinkle top with vanilla wafer crumbs and top with maraschino cherries. Refrigerate overnight. Cut into squares and serve.

title: grilled deer roast
directions: Cut foil to excess length of roast and form bowl to place meat in.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Wrap roast with bacon; place in foil.
Salt and pepper top.
Seal the foil.
Place on preheated grill for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Check to see if done.
Serve with rolls, baked beans, slaw, chips and barbecue sauce.

title: cheesecake #3
directions: Crust:
Combine melted butter and crushed graham cracker crumbs.
Pat evenly into bottom and about 1 inch up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and simmer 15 minutes.
This sauce is very good on shredded roast beef.

title: salmon-cheese loaf
directions: Mix all together in a mixing bowl.
Place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until done and golden brown on top.
Turn out on platter and top with cream sauce.

title: green rice
directions: Cook onions, green peppers and garlic in oleo.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Add eggs, salt, oil and onion mixture.
Stir in cheese.
Place in casserole dish; spread chicken soup over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: philly cheese steak
directions: Heat skillet with 2 tablespoons oil. Put in meat and season to taste. Put in mushrooms and onions. Then add teriyaki sauce to taste (4 dashes). Cook until desired doneness. Slice open hoagie buns and toast in broiler until lightly browned. Lay on a cookie sheet the opened bun. Layer cheese on bottom, then meat mixture and another layer of cheese. Pop into oven to melt cheese. Put on top bun and slice sandwich in half for better handling.

title: strawberries in the snow (sugar free)
directions: Crumble cake into 9 inch square pan. Mix 2 packages Equal into soften cream cheese then fold into Cool Whip. Fold mixture into crumbled cake and pat down to cover bottom of pan. Mix sliced strawberries into glaze and spread over top of cake mixture.

title: hot monterrey rice salad
directions: Cook meat.
Add other ingredients in a large bowl.
Add chips last.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions, drain.
Add beans and catsup.
Cut biscuits in half.
Place around dish, on top of meat and ingredients.
Add cheese in middle.
Bake until biscuits and cheese are brown and done through, at 350° for 20 minutes or so.

title: scalloped peppers
directions: Mix green peppers, cheese, margarine, evaporated milk and cracker crumbs in a greased casserole dish. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: african chow mein
directions: Blend together in baking dish.
Cook 1 hour in 350° oven. Cover with foil.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: mushroom appetizer squares
directions: Separate dough into 2 long rectangles.
Press onto bottom and 1/2 inch high around sides of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Toss mushrooms with margarine; arrange on dough.
Sprinkle with cheese and seasonings.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares. Serve warm.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: lady in waiting lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice to taste in mixing bowl. Mix to thick consistency.
Usually 2 to 3 minutes on low with mixer or by hand.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Cover with vanilla wafer cookies.
Cover and chill for 6 to 8 hours.
Serves 8.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cornstarch, salt, milk and vanilla. Then add
melted margarine and coconut.
Bake in unbaked pie crust until done, about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan; spread evenly so bottom is covered.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: martha pafford's turnips and pigs' tails
directions: Wash and clean pigs' tails.
Wash and cut up salad; peel roots and cut up, placing all in the pot with the pigs' tails.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Salt to taste.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Put all ingredients into a food processor and mix.

title: jello salad
directions: Set partially Jell-O and water.
Fold in sour cream, miniature marshmallows and fruit.
Place in a fancy bowl.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix in another bowl the remaining ingredients.
Pour one half of cake batter into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Pour on remaining batter.
Swirl with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Ice while hot with:

title: custard rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour until well mixed.
Pour over rhubarb.

title: aloha cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Do not use mixer.
Roll in 2 cups chopped pecans.

title: chocolate cake(no fat, no cholesterol)
directions: Spray 9 x 11-inch baking pan with Pam.
In a bowl, mix (beat just until blended) water, corn syrup and egg whites.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, cornstarch, baking soda and salt (which have been blended together); beat.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after cooled, or frost (frosting will change fat and cholesterol).

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Blend the first six ingredients together; set aside.
Blend remaining ingredients together; remove 1/2 cup chocolate mixture and set aside.
Blend both mixtures together.

title: meat balls
directions: In a large kettle, pour tomato juice and water.
When boiling, add balls of the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for three hours. Can also be cooked in a slow oven at 325° for about 2 hours. Makes 20 large meat balls.

title: preacher's fillets
directions: Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in catsup, water and soup mix; blend in crumbs and meat.
Shape into 1-inch thick patties and wrap a slice of bacon around each patty.
Grill in oven broiler or over open flame.

title: beef in creamy mushroom sauce
directions: Stir cornstarch into 1 cup water; reserve.
Trim fat from beef.
Cut beef into thin strips, about 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch.

title: north carolina slaw
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar.
Cook over low heat.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour sugar and vinegar over mixture.
Set in refrigerator.
Will last for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: stew for all occasions(serves 8)
directions: Best if made a day or two ahead.

title: forgotten dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
The egg whites must be at room temperature.
Whip the 5 egg whites and salt until frothy.
Beat the cream of tartar until it stands in peaks (not dry).
Add the sugar, a teaspoon at a time, beating at medium speed.
Add vanilla; continue beating.
Beat at low speed for 20 minutes, and place in greased 8 x 12-inch baking pan, spreading evenly.
After the oven has been preheated, turn off and place the pan in the oven.
Leave overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Soak bananas in pineapple juice to prevent from turning dark. Any fresh fruit may be used.
Drain well before mixing.

title: cream of cucumber soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add seeded cucumber chunks, broth, vinegar and herb.
Bring to a boil and stir in farina.
Simmer, partially covered, for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Puree, then return to soup pot.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: toffee squares
directions: In a bowl, cream the butter and sugar well. Add egg and beat. Add vanilla. Stir.
Add flour and salt.
Mix. Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread with melted chocolate. Sprinkle with nuts. Cut while warm into bars.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze all water from spinach.
Chop water chestnuts and onions.
Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Steam peas in a small amount of water until tender, about 3 minutes.
Remove core from lettuce.
Wash and pat dry.
With a sharp knife, shred lettuce into 1/4-inch slices.
In a glass bowl, place the ingredients in this order: lettuce, scallions and green pepper.
Spread top with mayonnaise and sprinkle with sugar, Cheddar cheese and bacon.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Add beans, ketchup, chili powder, oregano, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: rocky road squares
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chips with milk and butter. Remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine peanuts and marshmallows. Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread on waxed paper lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Cover and store at room temperature.
Makes 40.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake at 400° until done.
Sprinkle sugar on top of rolled dough before baking if desired.

title: popcorn candy
directions: Mix together popcorn, Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Melt almond bark and peanut butter.
Pour over top popcorn mixture.
Spread in thin layer on wax paper.
When hard, break into hard pieces.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream shortening.
Add flour and
sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan, making a rim around
edge.
Bake
at
for 25 minutes or until crust is golden.
Meanwhile,
beat
the 4 eggs slightly.
Add 2 cups sugar and the lemon juice.
Fold in flour and baking powder.	Pour over baked
crust and bake for another 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.
Sprinkle
with
sugar
and
cut
into squares.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover bottom of large baking pan with asparagus.
Spread over this the toasted cubes of bread, egg slices, soup mixture and cheese.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake for 30 minutes and serve hot.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and mix. Bake in oven at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: pepper hash
directions: Use coarse grinding blade and grind all together.
Then cook all together for one hour.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cover bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish with broccoli. Place chicken pieces on top.
Mix chicken soup and milk.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs and shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice pilaf.

title: nutty sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, white sugar, eggs, milk, salt, vanilla, cinnamon and 1/3 stick oleo in a large bowl and mix well. Put mixture in 2 quart baking dish.
Make topping using brown sugar, flour, pecans and 1/3 stick oleo and place on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Add Eagle Brand milk, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Prepare banana pudding as usual.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Cook and bone chicken. Reserve 1 cup chicken broth. Combine soups, green chilies, spices, Tabasco sauce and chicken broth in double boiler. Blend well.

title: mom's chili
directions: Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
If too thick, add some water or more chicken broth.
Can also add small pieces of ham.
Add cornstarch just before removing from heat.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread into oblong pan (cookie sheet) and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (no longer). Watch carefully; it will burn quickly.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook until hard boil.
Add cornstarch mixed with water.
Beat. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour in pan and let cool.
Cut.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix other ingredients well with dry ingredients.
Then pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 375° approximately 1 hour or until done.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain well.
Mix with other ingredients.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until firm on a greased cookie sheet (can do night before).
Yields 48 appetizers.

title: bean salad
directions: Bring sugar, oil and vinegar to a boil.
Place vegetables in large bowl and toss good.
Pour liquid over vegetables and toss again.

title: presto chicken
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup and dressing in baking dish.
Add chicken.
Cover; bake for 40 minutes, or until done, at 350°. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: velvet salad
directions: Mix dry Jello, pineapple, sour cream, Cool Whip and nuts together. Chill in mold before serving.

title: caribbean chicken and rice arroz con pollo
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces; rub with salt and pepper. Refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
In heavy kettle, brown ham and chicken, cook 5 minutes over low heat, add all ingredients and saute for 10 minutes.
Stir well, drain peas, add 2 1/2 cups of water and follow directions on package of rice.
Add all ingredients, cover, cook low heat.
Cook for 40 minutes, add peas and pimentos.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Arrange stalks in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch Pyrex dish with flowerets facing outward. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken. Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus,
place in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Pour a small amount of soup over asparagus; place sliced eggs on top of soup.
Spoon tuna over eggs;
add rest of soup.
Top with cheese. Bake uncovered at 325° for 20 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: cottage cheese roast
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg and mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla and rum flavored extracts.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with "Vanilla-Nutmeg Sauce."

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add sugar (cream).
Beat eggs in.
Add flour, alternating with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350°.
Pour into three 9-inch pans, greased and floured.

title: louisiana chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove to casserole.
In hot drippings on medium heat, stir flour.
Cook until brown.
Add celery, peppers and onions.
Cook until tender, stirring often.
Stir in bouillon, water, salt and hot pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8-inch square pan or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples. Combine flour, brown sugar and butter.
Spread mixture over sugared apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until fruit is tender and top is golden brown.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Have cookie sheets ready.
Mix flour and baking soda.
Beat peanut butter, butter, sugars and vanilla with electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
With mixer on low speed, gradually beat in flour mixture.

title: pickles
directions: Pour off juice from pickles and add clove and water.
Boil. Add sugar.
Let cool.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand overnight.

title: reuben dip
directions: Simmer all together and serve on bread or crackers.

title: blackberry creek farm eggplant
directions: Dice eggplant (4 1/2 or 5 cups).
Simmer for 8 minutes in boiling water with herb and salt. Drain. Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add eggplant with parsley. Combine melted butter and crumbs.
In a 9-inch baking dish, layer eggplant and crumbs.
Pour cream over top. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: smokin' cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage and carrots into small pieces about the size of rice kernels (the food processor makes this job easier). In salad bowl, combine the sugar, salt, pepper, milk, mayonnaise, buttermilk, vinegar and lemon juice. Beat until smooth. Add the cabbage and carrots. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into sticks about 3/8-inch thick so they resemble French fries. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roll in flour, then dip in beaten egg and water. Roll in bread crumbs and fry in skillet in hot margarine until golden brown, about 8 minutes. Drain on paper towel and serve hot.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain the pineapple and save 6 tablespoons of juice.
Combine with sugar and flour.
Add cheese, pineapple and melted butter. Top with crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and baking powder together and set aside. Cream softened oleo by hand.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well after each.
Add milk and flour alternately; blend.
Add sour cream, bananas and nuts.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes until it tests done with toothpick.
Very good.

title: hot dill pickles
directions: Wash and dry cucumbers.
Place 4 into each of 4 (1-quart) sterilized jars.
Into each jar, place 2 tablespoons dill seed, 1 teaspoon caraway seed, 1/2 teaspoon garlic and 1/4 teaspoon crushed red peppers.
In large saucepan, bring water to a boil. Add vinegar, salt and alum.
Pour over cucumbers to cover, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Seal with lids.
Process in water bath for 15 minutes.
Let stand at least 8 weeks before serving.
Yield: 4 quarts.

title: raspberry roll
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1 1/2 cups water; cook 5 minutes. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: chocolate syrup(fat free)
directions: In small pot, bring sugar and water to a boil.
Whisk in cocoa, vanilla, salt and corn syrup.
Continue whisking until all of the solids have dissolved.
Reduce sauce until slightly thickened.
Strain.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into squeeze bottles.
Squeeze into cold milk or over ice cream.

title: apple-cheese pleasers
directions: Mix together and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes at 375°.

title: wine cookies
directions: Mix wine, sugar, oil and anise seed.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Roll and shape as you like.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: oriental peas
directions: Saute together 4 minutes the onion, celery and butter.
Add water chestnuts, mushrooms, soy sauce and peas.
Heat a few minutes and serve.

title: baked beans(beans for 50)
directions: Soak beans overnight. Add all ingredients and water. Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: quesadilla(low-fat)
directions: Place 2 tortillas on an ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Sprinkle with mild green chilies and salsa. Top with remaining tortillas.
Bake at 450° for 4 minutes on each side.
To serve, cut each tortilla into 8 wedges.
Yields 16 wedges with 37 calories each wedge and 1.7 g fat.

title: raisin m-m-mumbles
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients all together until raisins are done, 5 to 10 minutes. Add the sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened.
Let cool while making crust.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches and pineapple.
Add dry mix and Tang.
Stir in thawed berries.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In bowl, combine eggs and Parmesan cheese.
In medium skillet, scramble eggs in melted butter.
Place 1 slice of ham on each muffin half.
Top with 1/4 of scrambled egg, 2 tablespoons pizza sauce and 1 slice of Swiss and American cheese.
Broil about 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: hash brown potatoes casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.

title: squash bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix dry ingredients, except sugar, thoroughly.
Beat eggs until frothy. Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until lemon colored, 3 minutes . Stir in squash.
Add dry ingredients and mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes. Cool on rack.
Remove from pan after 10 minutes.

title: marmalade salad
directions: Crumble crackers.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Save a cup of crumbs to spread over top when finished.
Mix remaining ingredients and place on top of crust and sprinkle with remaining Ritz crackers.
Chill at least 2 hours and then ready to serve.

title: seafood salad
directions: Rinse macaroni with cold water and drain again.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, grated onion, white pepper, salt, celery seed and dry mustard.
Fold mayonnaise mixture into macaroni.
Gently fold in imitation crab meat.
If not moist enough, add more mayonnaise and sour cream.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pink lemonade cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions; bake in 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round cake pans.
Cool.
Stir ice cream to soften; quickly stir in red food coloring and 1/2 cup of lemonade concentrate.
Spread evenly in foil-lined 9 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pan.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours, until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, salt, syrup, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 50 more minutes, until firm.

title: chicken a la special
directions: Bone and remove skin from the chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt butter or margarine in large skillet.
Saute chicken until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes, turning occasionally.
Add carrot sticks, lifting chicken so the chicken is on top of the carrots.
Add 1/8 to 1/4 cup water.
Cover and steam for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken and carrots are tender.
Ten minutes before chicken is done, cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Remove chicken to a warm platter or serving casserole.
Arrange carrots on ends of a large platter and the broccoli on the sides.
Put chicken in the middle, covering the broccoli stalks.
Keep warm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together soup and sour cream. Pour over hash browns.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese is golden brown and bubbly.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix together; put on top and sides of frosting.

title: lettuce and cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in large bowl as listed; let set overnight.
Stir just before serving.

title: honey milk balls
directions: Mix honey and peanut butter.
Gradually add dry milk, mix well. Form into balls with greased hands.
Roll in crushed cereal. Chill until firm.
Yields 30.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla together using mixer.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon to mixture.
Mix well by hand.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
While hot, sprinkle with sugar.

title: rocky road cake
directions: In a small bowl, stir together nuts, raisins, marshmallows and chocolate pieces; set aside.
In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat cake mix, eggs, mayonnaise and water until blended. Increase speed to medium.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in nut mixture. Grease and flour a large tube pan.
Pour in
batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on wire rack.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice to heat.
Heat pineapple juice and 1 cup buttermilk to boiling point.
While liquid is heating, put Jell-O in large mixing bowl.
Pour hot liquid over Jell-O and dissolve thoroughly, then add another cup buttermilk.
Let cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Then, add remaining ingredients and a few drops of almond extract.
Mix thoroughly.
Let set in refrigerator about 5 minutes, then pour into desired mold(s). Makes about 16 individual molds.
Keeps well and can be frozen.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Roll into small balls and bake in hot oven (400° to 425°) for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: helen's baked beans
directions: Pour all ingredients except brown sugar and pineapple slices over beans and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Heat oven to 375°; put ingredients in an uncovered casserole and bake for 30 minutes.
Place pineapple slices on top and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: nutty spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Garnish with a few chopped nuts. Serve with fresh vegetables or stuff into cherry tomatoes or mushroom caps.

title: hermit cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Add fruit previously cut and floured.
Add salt, flour and flavorings, cut nuts and applesauce.
Bake 3 hours at 250°.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Cook berries and water together and strain.
Then add sugar and cook for 10 or 15 minutes.
Pour in dish to set.

title: grammy gayman's no fail pie crust(makes dough for 2 pies or 1 double crust pie.)
directions: (May add a teaspoon of sugar for fruit pies.)
Mix flour and Crisco to form small pea-sized pieces.
Add water; mix.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll each on floured surface.
(May be refrigerated for later use.)

title: heavenly cherry angel food trifle
directions: Combine pudding and Cool Whip. Then combine the cake cubes. Put layer of cake cubes in glass bowl, then layer of pie filling and sprinkle almonds; repeat over and over.

title: apple-cinnamon cake
directions: Slice apples. Spread in sprayed oblong dish. Add water and sugar. Sprinkle cinnamon over this. Add cake mix on top. Sprinkle again with cinnamon. Add pecans. Slice margarine on top. Bake as is at 350° to 375° about 35 minutes. Cool. Cover with frozen topping, thawed.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Put vanilla bean in the bottom of 1 gallon jug (dark brown jug if available).
Use a funnel and add coffee, sugar and boiling water, then add vodka.
Invert once or twice.
Invert weekly.
Let set 2 to 4 weeks before drinking.
Store in a dark cool place. Enjoy!

title: fudge
directions: Combine semi-sweet chocolate chips, sweet cooking chocolate, marshmallow cream and walnuts in large bowl.
Combine sugar, salt, butter and milk in large, heavy saucepan; heat to boiling stirring constantly.
Boil 6 minutes, stirring often.
Pour at once over chocolate mixture in bowl.
Stir vigorously with wooden spoon until chocolate is melted and mixture is creamy.
Pour into buttered shallow pan 13 x 9 x 2-inches; let stand a few hours to set.
Cut into squares and store in tightly covered metal box.

title: the greatest fruit slush you ever tasted!
directions: Dissolve the sugar in the boiling water. Add the orange juice. Add 6 ounces water, pineapple, cherries and bananas.
Mix all ingredients and put in freezer in individual cups for serving or freeze in large container.
Check, stir and taste once an hour. Put in small dishes now!
Thaw slightly before serving. Great for warm (hot?!) summer evenings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni following package direction. Drain. Return macaroni to pan immediately. Stir contents of cheese packet into hot macaroni. Blend well. In large bowl combine remaining ingredients with macaroni; toss with fork and season to taste. Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, peanut butter and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Bake at 350° on middle shelf until golden brown.

title: pan-fried onion dip
directions: Cut the onions in half and then slice them into 1/8 inch thick half-rounds.
(You will have about 3 cups of onions.)
Heat the butter and oil in a large saute pan over medium heat.
Add the onions, cayenne, salt, and pepper and saute for 10 minutes.
Reduce the heat to medium low and cook stirring occasionally, for 20 more minutes until the onions are browned and caramelized.
Allow the onions to cool.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Add all ingredients, except baking soda.
Add small amount of thick milk, which you mix and add later.

title: sunday dinner fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper in a plastic bag. Shake to mix.
Place 2 or 3 pieces of chicken in bag.
Shake well. Repeat procedure.
Heat oil and oleo in a large skillet. Add chicken and brown on both sides over high heat (375°). Cover, reduce heat to medium and cook 20 minutes.

title: phyllo chicken
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place one sheet phyllo in dish; brush with oleo.
Repeat with 5 more sheets of phyllo, keeping other covered to prevent drying.
In a bowl, mix chicken, bacon, broccoli and cheese; spread over phyllo.
In another bowl, whisk eggs, milks, salt and pepper; pour over chicken.
Cover filling with one phyllo sheet, brush with oleo. Repeat with rest of phyllo.
Brush top with remaining oleo.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: venison with sour cream
directions: Cut venison into pieces and melt fat in heavy frying pan.
Add meat and garlic.
Brown on all sides and arrange in dish.
Put vegetables in remaining fat and cook for 2 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and water.
Pour over meat.
Bake in slow oven until meat is tender.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light colored.
Add sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour in pie crust.
Beat egg whites.

title: chicken breast with sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a shallow dish so that pieces do not overlap.
Cover with mushrooms.
Combine undiluted mushroom soup, sherry and sour cream.
Stir until well blended.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken, covering.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Goes well over rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together thoroughly. Press into loaf pan (8 x 4-inch).
Bake 1 hour until juice is clear.
Drain; let stand 5 or 10 minutes and serve.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar until smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and stir into mixture.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla. Bake in buttered pie pan or 8-inch square pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve cold with whipped cream.

title: chewies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, add egg, flour, stir well.
Add vanilla and pecans, stir well.
Put in greased pan and bake in 325° oven for 25 - 30 minutes
This recipe may be doubled.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In saucepan, saute onions in margarine until tender.
Reduce heat; add milk, cream cheese and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli.
Microwave for 5 minutes before adding salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: south of the border lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add tomatoes, picante sauce, taco mix and chilies. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Spread half of mixture in bottom of oblong pan. Top with half the noodles. Spread half the Ricotta cheese on noodles and top with Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers and end with Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crustless pumpkin pie(makes 6 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in 9-inch pie pan sprayed with release agent.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and then at 350° for 45 minutes.
Check for doneness after the first 45 minutes. (Some ovens may vary.)

title: festive coffee cake
directions: Mix dry mixes, add oil and sour cream and blend together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sprinkle a Bundt pan with cinnamon and sugar.
Add batter and sprinkle top of cake with cinnamon and sugar. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes. Turn out on serving plate and sprinkle with more cinnamon and sugar.
Keep in a closed container.
This cake is better the second day.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: e-z peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly and pour into buttered pan.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples until tender and mushy before adding spices and sugar.
After adding sugar and spices, cook about 11 or 12 hours on high.
Stir occasionally, leaving lid cracked open after adding sugar and spices.
Put into jars and seal.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Flour chicken and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Brown in skillet with oil. Remove and place in shallow baking dish. Discard excess oil.
Add chicken broth and lemon juice to skillet and heat.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with parsley flakes and capers. Heat in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cherry cherry pie
directions: Dissolve arrowroot powder in cherry juice and water.
Cook until thickened, adding another cup of juice.
Then add sour cherries, honey and almond extract.
Let simmer 1 minute.
Cool. Pour into baked Stir-N-Roll Pie Crust Shell.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Serve with homemade ice cream or fresh grated coconut.

title: kraut supreme
directions: Drain kraut and mix the pimento, celery, onions and pepper. Bring to a rolling boil the sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Pour this over the first mixture and let cool. Refrigerate 24 hours, then serve.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Shape sausage into balls, brown and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to simmer, cover and heat through.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut into bite size pieces. Cook broccoli. Grease casserole dish and spread broccoli on the bottom. Sprinkle with cheese and add the chicken. Sprinkle with more cheese. Mix soup, mayonnaise , sour cream, Cheddar cheese, lemon juice, curry powder, salt and pepper to taste. Pour mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, paprika and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: very good chicken casserole
directions: Cut potatoes and carrots into chunks; put into pan with water. Cook while you prepare other ingredients.
In large skillet, add oil and heat.
Wash and cut chicken into 2-inch pieces.
Coat in flour mixture.
Add to oil; brown on all sides.
When browned, put into large casserole dish.
Add chopped onions to skillet and saute.
Add the broth and soup to onions and heat.
Also, add 1 can water.
Put potatoes and carrots into casserole.
Pour heated onion mixture over the chicken, potatoes and carrots.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add all other ingredients.
Beat well and cook very slowly until it thickens.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar first.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, one cup at a time; add flavoring.
Do not beat over 4 minutes.
Grease and flour pan.
Preheat oven for 5 minutes at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.
If browning too fast, place a pan of water under cake.

title: frozen pumpkin parfait squares
directions: Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup melted butter; press into a 9-inch square pan.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter and mix with remaining ingredients.
Fold in fruit gently.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: rigatoni and meat sauce
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, combine Italian sausage, onion and garlic. Cook until sausage is no longer pink.
Drain. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, sugar, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Prepare rigatoni according to package directions; drain.
Serve with meat sauce. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: sandy's e~z cheese ball
directions: Cream together, form a ball, roll in nuts. Refrigerate.

title: hearty up north beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Brown Mexican sausage (remove casing).
Saut onion and both peppers in butter.
Mix all together and simmer, simmer, simmer.

title: stewed tomato casserole
directions: Place the tomatoes, butter and sugar in a saucepan and heat until the margarine melts.

Add bread crumbs and continue simmering until most of liquid is absorbed, about 15 minutes. Turn the mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart round casserole and bake in a 350° oven until thick and bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, sugar and molasses together.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cake cool.

title: the impossible pie
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in blender.
Blend 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch glass or Corning Ware pan. Sprinkle coconut or nuts over top.
Press down into filling with fingertips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken broth and vegetables in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in chicken soup, chicken and pepper.
Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: dennis floge's world famous "buck shot chili"
directions: Saute the chopped onion and garlic cloves in the chopped bacon fat until tender.
Then add the ground beef and cook until browned.
Add the tomatoes and kidney beans, salt, bay leaf and chili powder.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for about 1 hour or so until desired thickness.

title: quick english peas
directions: In a saucepan, heat the soup and cheese.
Stir until the cheese is melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add the peas and serve. Serves 8.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, vanilla, brown sugar and milk.
Add 1 egg.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, chocolate chips and pecans.
Blend well. Drop round tablespoonfuls 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool 2 minutes on pan.

title: baked pork chops and mushroom soup
directions: Brown pork chops in a little oil.
After browning, put in a baking pan and pour mushroom soup over chops (spread soup around to cover chops good).
You can add onions also for added flavor. Bake at 350° for about an hour or until done.
This is good with mashed potatoes because the soup is going to make a tasty gravy.

title: low-fat chicken meal in a pot
directions: Note:
Canned peas and carrots may be substituted, 2 cans drained.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until smooth. Beat in egg yolks.
Alternate flour and milk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three layers for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Place in a large pie plate.
Top with lettuce, cheese and tomato.
Serve with Tostitos plain chips.

title: tofu cheesecake
directions: Blend until all ingredients are smooth.
Pour into crust and bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with strawberries or other fruit as desired.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Melt butter and honey; add molasses.
Pour mixture over popcorn and toss.
Place mixture in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: salt rising bread
directions: Place the ingredients in saucepan and mix together. Place lid on saucepan and place in oven with light on overnight. Don't take out of oven until a white foam forms on top of mixture. Remove pan from oven. Remove potatoes and add enough flour to make batter just thick enough to drop off spoon. Put lid back on pan and place back in oven to rise an hour or longer, until it rises to top of pan.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Add flour, mushroom soup and mushrooms. Bring to a boil; turn off. Take a casserole dish and put 1 layer chicken, then a layer of rice. Pour some of the sauce over them. Repeat this again.
On top of this put 1 cup sharp Cheddar cheese. Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mocha punch
directions: In a large container, combine coffee and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Immediately before serving, pour into a punch bowl.
Add milk and mix well.
Top with scoops of ice cream and stir well.
Yield:
3 quarts.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients, sour cream and bananas.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 375° for one hour or until done.

title: avocado salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Combine avocado, onion and tomato.
Add dressing and marinate in refrigerator at least 30 minutes.
Spoon salad onto a bed of lettuce using a slotted spoon.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix hamburger, cracker crumbs, 1 cup milk, salt, onion and pepper and let stand overnight.
Cut in pieces and roll in flour and fry.
Pour 1 can mushroom soup and 1 can milk mixed together and pour over pieces arranged in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: play dough
directions: Stir together and knead.

title: no bake peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips and paraffin.
Make small balls and place on toothpicks.
Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls in melted chocolate.
Let stand and cool on wax paper.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Open crescent rolls and press together on a cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: brown bread
directions: Combine sugar and flour, then add baking soda to buttermilk and mix.
Add bran flakes, nuts and raisins.
Pour into one 8 x 3 1/4 x 2 1/2 well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini and tomatoes with basil
directions: Peel tomatoes; slice.
Scrub zucchini and slice.
Peel onions and chop fine.
Put a layer of tomatoes in a shallow baking dish. Season with salt.
Cover with zucchini and sprinkle with onions; salt.
Cover zucchini with a layer of tomatoes.
Season with salt. Pour oil over vegetables.
Add basil to vegetables tucking it underneath tomatoes.
Put in a prepared 375° oven for 40 minutes or until vegetables begin to brown and juice cooks down a bit.
A sprinkle of chopped fresh basil and parsley over vegetables at serving time makes it attractive.
Can also top with Parmesan cheese.

title: hot buttered nog
directions: Combine eggnog and milk; slowly beat in sweet vermouth.
Stir in salt and coriander; heat gently to just below boiling.
Pour into preheated cups or mugs and top each with 1/2 teaspoon soft butter.
Makes about 16 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine; add other ingredients one at a time.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 40 minutes in 300° oven.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal, salt and shortening. Dissolve brown sugar and yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. When mixture is cool, add yeast mixture.
Add flour, beating after each addition.
Knead for 10 minutes.
May have to add more flour if it is too sticky.
Let rise twice.
Make into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no peek chicken(quick and easy)
directions: Mix rice, mushroom soup, cream of celery soup and water together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with soup mix.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Do not lift foil or peek!

title: chicken supreme
directions: *Breasts, boned, may be used for a party service.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly jelled.
Combine all other ingredients; fold fruit into gelatin mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Can also be frozen.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in double boiler over low heat to melt, then cool.
Next, pour buttermilk in mixture and stir in Cool Whip.
Stir well.
Add nuts.
Congeal.

title: tofu herb spread
directions: Place the garlic, basil, parsley, celery and chives in a food processor and chop until fine.
Add the remaining ingredients and process until creamy.
Yield: approximately 2 cups.

title: lasagna in a bun
directions: Cut thin slices off tops of buns.
Hollow out centers, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells.
In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, garlic powder and Italian seasoning. Cook 4 to 5 minutes or until heated through.
Meanwhile, combine Parmesan, half of Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese; mix well.	Spoon meat sauce into buns; top with cheese mixture.
Place on baking sheet and cover loosely with foil.	Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes or until the cheese melts.

title: quick and easy pie crust
directions: Blend flour and salt in bowl.
Pour cooking oil and cold water all at once into the flour mixture.
Stir with fork until mixture forms ball in the bowl.
Divide into 2 balls for bottom and top crust.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease pan.
Arrange crescent rolls in pan by patting out to cover pan.
Sprinkle browned sausage, hash browns and cheese on top of rolls.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese; pour on top of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mem's pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight in cold water.
Next morning, drain and put peas in a large pan.
Add ham bone, diced onion and carrot.
Cover ingredients with water and add salt, pepper and hominy (drain and rinse hominy before adding to soup).
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer until peas and carrot are cooked.
While soup is cooking, be sure that your ingredients are just covered with water. Usually takes about 1 1/2 hours.
About 15 minutes before soup is done, add the rice.

title: lemon chiffon pudding(good)
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cream together butter and flour mixture. Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add yolks and milk.
Gradually add lemon juice and rind.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry; fold in carefully.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Place in pan with 1 inch of hot water.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Boil florets until soft in 1/2 cup water.
Process in food processor or blender.
Heat margarine.
Add flour; stir in broth. Mix.
Add vegetables (rest of ingredients) and cook together. Makes 2 large servings.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown the rice in the cooking oil.
Drain off the oil; stir in all other ingredients, except water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add water and bring to a boil.
When it begins to boil, lower the heat and cover.
Do not stir the rice mixture after this.
Simmer until all the water is absorbed, 30 to 45 minutes. Serve hot.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix buttermilk, eggs, salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon of the flour. Dip onion rings into mixture, then in flour. Fry in hot oil.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl beat flour, 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/3 cup margarine.
Blend 2 to 3 minutes or until particles are fine.
Pat firmly into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with pecans and press lightly.

title: 5 day pickles
directions: Bring salt, water and vinegar to boil and cool.
Put 8 grape leaves in bottom of jar; add 1/2 the dill and garlic, then sliced cucumbers.
(I cut mine the long way.)
Bring salt, water and vinegar to a boil.
Cool.
Add garlic, dill and grape leaves last. Fill jar with brine.
Put cloth over the top.
Let stand in refrigerator for 5 days.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Combine corn, green pepper, pimiento, celery, cucumber and onion and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours or overnight.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rocky road parfaits(children's)
directions: Prepare pudding mix in bowl, using package directions.
Chill in refrigerator.
Spoon layers of pudding and marshmallow cream into 4 parfait glasses, beginning and ending with pudding.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle almonds on top.

title: hash brown potatoes (baked)
directions: Combine hash browns, onions, chicken soup, cheese and sour cream. Mix together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased 13 x 9 pan. Top with corn flakes. Do Not Cover.

title: all in one camp breakfast
directions: Cut bacon into 2-inch pieces.
Fry crisp.
Reserve 3 tablespoons bacon grease.
Cut potatoes into cubes.
Saute vegetables in the bacon grease until cooked through.
Blend the beaten eggs and seasonings into vegetables.
Stir gently until desired doneness.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Serves 2.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine yeast in a bowl and add sugar and small amount of water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add salt, egg and remaining water. Sift flour; add half to mixture and beat well.
Add melted butter and mix in as much flour as can be stirred with a spoon.
Let rise and punch down.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator.
Use as much as desired.
Grease pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Brush with butter after 15 minutes.

title: picante sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, mix all ingredients bringing to a boil. Simmer for 1 hour; pour in jars and seal.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Cook broccoli and rice as directed on package.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into cooked rice and broccoli.
Sprinkle paprika on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots; cool and drain.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and chill well.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in bite size pieces and cook in small amount of water for five minutes.
Drain.
Mix cream of chicken soup, onion, pimento, carrots, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Fold in zucchini. Melt margarine and add to stuffing mix.
Line casserole with stuffing, reserving small amount for top.
Pour in zucchini mixture.
Top with stuffing and sprinkle with toasted almonds. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over chicken pieces in non-metal dish.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Turn occasionally. Use marinade to baste chicken when barbecuing.

title: pioneer bread pudding(a good way to use up crusts and stale bread...)
directions: Place bread in a buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Scald milk with butter and sugar.
Beat eggs lightly; stir in warm milk and vanilla.
Pour mixture over bread.
Set the baking dish in a pan of warm water up to level of the pudding.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar. Beat egg yolks.
Add buttermilk to egg yolks.
Add this mixture to flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add melted butter and mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold them into flour mixture.
Fry on hot, well-greased griddle.
Makes 12 to 15 pancakes.

title: beef stroganoff(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Cut steak into 1/4-inch strips.
Coat with salt and pepper. Drop into bottom of slow cooker with onion.
Mix garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon and catsup.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until tender.
Turn control to high.
Add mushrooms.
Dissolve flour in small amount of water. Add to meat mixture, stirring, until blended.
Cook on high for 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in sour cream; turn off heat.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening; add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
In medium bowl, sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Combine the pumpkin and milk.
Stir in baking soda.
Add flour and pumpkin mixtures alternately to shortening sugar mixture, beating well after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Turn batter in prepared baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Frost with Raisin-Brown Sugar Icing.

title: fancy potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes in salted water until done.
Cool and peel. Grate the potatoes.
Combine potatoes, onions, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and salt.
Place in greased baking pan.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle on top of the potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, until hot and bubbling in the middle.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Put in refrigerator.
Cover with wrap and plate.
Roll out and decorate. It's best with red hots and colored sugar.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 8 minutes.

title: norwegian flat bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add enough white flour to roll, approximately 3 cups.
Take a piece of the dough and roll out on floured board until very thin.
Using a lefse turner, put onto grill and cook on both sides.
Have oven warmed to 250°. When one piece
of flat bread has been cooked, put it into the oven to dry out.
When the next piece has been cooked, remove the one from the oven and continue in this fashion until all dough is used. Store in a pasteboard box.
Keeps well.
I break the large piece into smaller pieces for storing.

title: cotton patch oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine buttermilk, sugar and egg.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat until blended.
Spoon mixture into greased muffin tins.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot with margarine.

title: p.t.a. cookies
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Cream the butter, sugar and egg.
Break mincemeat and add to dry ingredients.
Blend with sugar mixture. Chill 2 hours in refrigerator.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400° on greased cookie sheet.

title: sausage snacks
directions: Separate crescent dough into 4 triangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Brush each with butter.
Combine cheese and oregano and sprinkle over dough.
Cut each rectangle crosswise to form 2 squares.
Bake sausage links on each square; roll up.
Cut each roll into 3 or 4 pieces and secure each with a toothpick.
Place, cut side down, on a baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat together milk, eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Stir in bread crumbs (bisciuts).
Pour mixture into 1 or 2-quart baking dish, greased with vegetable shortening.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clear.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in large bowl the flour and sugar.
Bring to boil the oleo, oil, water and Quik.
Pour mixture over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and baking soda.
Bake in shallow pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, water and eggs for 3 minutes.
Add oil and mix for 1 minute.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Punch holes with fork in top of cake.
While hot, combine powdered sugar and lemon juice and dribble over top.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole(great when you want the taste of chicken and dressing)
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove from broth and save 2 2/3 cups of broth.
Bone chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Set aside. Combine 1/2 of the broth with the chicken soup.
Set aside. Combine remaining 1/2 of the broth with the mushroom soup.
Set aside.
Melt the butter and pour over the stuffing and toss until all of it is moist with butter.
Set aside 1/4 cup for topping (garnish).

title: garlic sauce(salsa di aglio)
directions: Mash garlic to a paste with the salt.
Add olive oil to garlic, a little at a time.
Mix in lemon juice and parsley.
Then add anchovies, if desired.
Whisk in an electric blender (not necessary).
Pour over spaghetti.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, mix shortening, applesauce, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla until shortening breaks into pea size pieces. Add flour mixture to applesauce mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: noodles with cottage cheese
directions: In blender (or food processor), combine egg, milk, cottage cheese and seasonings until a thin mixture.
In large frying pan, melt butter.
Add noodles which have been well drained and cook until slightly browned, stirring frequently.
Turn heat to low and stir in egg mixture to coat noodles.
Cook until set, about 20 minutes (don't stir).
Best served right away.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla, oil and eggs. Add flour, soda and salt into first mixture.
Fold in oats and then corn flakes.
Crush a little.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until brown.
Makes a dishpan full.

title: tender beef brisket
directions: Line a baking pan with enough heavy-duty aluminum foil to cover and seal the brisket which has been trimmed.
Place brisket, fat side down, on the foil.
Sprinkle salts heavily all over brisket.
Add liquid smoke.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with the foil.
Bake at 270° for 6 hours.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Put in freezer for 4 minutes until firm. Roll ball in pecans.

title: graham apple dessert
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Place apples in melted butter.
Sprinkle sugar, salt, cinnamon and nuts over apples.
Combine cracker crumbs and brown sugar and moisten with milk.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: coconut layer cake(makes 12 servings)
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°. Grease and flour three 8-inch round cake pans. Set pans aside. Beat eggs at high speed of an electric beater 2 minutes. Add sour cream and next 3 ingredients, beating well after each addition. Add cake mix. Beat at low speed until blended. Beat at high speed 2 minutes. Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake at 325° for 25 to 27 minutes. Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes. Remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks. Spread coconut cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup coconut left over from frosting.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage, bell pepper and onion in a large pot; drain.
Add cooking wine and spaghetti sauce packet; stir. Add tomato sauce and stewed tomatoes (crushed).
Add a jar of spaghetti sauce, Italian seasoning and garlic powder to taste. Let simmer on low for 10 to 15 minutes to allow seasoning to go through sauce.

title: dropped tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer; add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Add to mixture alternating with buttermilk, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove to racks to cool.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in Pam sprayed oblong casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes or until custardy in appearance at 350°.
Eat hot as accompaniment to the meal or cold as a dessert.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour 9-inch glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Mix and put in shallow baking dish or pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: maple cream cheese coffee treat
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine in a separate bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Flatten biscuits and spoon cream cheese mixture on biscuits.
Fold biscuits to overlap and pinch dough so cream cheese is sealed in the dough.
Place biscuits seam side down in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan 3 to 5 minutes before turning upside down on serving plate.
Best if served warm.
Great for breakfast!!

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese.
Bake until melted.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, corn flakes and vanilla; mix well.
Drop onto wax paper or foil with tablespoon.

title: squash souffle
directions: Melt butter in hot milk (microwave works well).
Pour over bread crumbs.
Mix with squash, salt, pepper, onion and eggs. Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with enough cheese to cover. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: light and fluffy pie
directions: Dissolve jello completely in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until jello is thickened, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using fork or wire whisk, blend in Cool Whip topping.
Whip until smooth.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 3 hours.

title: canachos(appetizers)
directions: Cut tortillas in triangles.
Chop lettuce, dice tomatoes and grate cheese.
In frying pan, heat refried beans.
Using deep fryer, fry tortillas until crispy.
Spread refried beans on each chip, then top off with cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and sliced jalapenos in that order.
Serve with cold beverage.

title: low-fat turkey chop suey
directions: In a large skillet, brown the ground turkey.
Drain off any fat.
Add the vegetables, ginger and all but 1/4 cup of the broth. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Combine the 1/4 cup of reserved broth with the soy sauce and cornstarch.
Add to the meat and vegetable mixture, stirring until thickened and bubbly.
Serve over the cooked brown rice.
Makes 6 servings, about 294 calories and 8 grams of fat.

title: gunnar's cheeseball
directions: Mix together and form ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: no-fat french vanilla coffee
directions: Microwave milk.
Mix the ingredients, adding vanilla last to keep from curdling.
Tastes as good as International.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Bring to a
boil
the sugar and water.	Add the rhubarb and simmer 3 to
4 minutes. Beat the eggs with the flour, then add liquid (only
from	the cooked rhubarb) to mixture.
Bring this to a
boil,
stir
constantly	until
it thickens.
Add a touch of red
coloring,
add rhubarb, stirring gently.
Do not cook.
Put into
10-inch
pie tin with your favorite pie crust recipe, but make a latticed crust on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at	350°
until
mixture
bubbles
clear
to the center of the pie.

title: sylvia's baked potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
In baking pan, add potatoes and pour the mixed ingredients over potatoes (coat them good).
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: garbanzo oat waffles
directions: Whiz ingredients in blender.
Preheat waffle iron and spray with nonstick spray.
Bake for 10 minutes or until steaming stops. Crispy, delicious waffles and "fat-free," so eat as many as you want.
You can cook them as pancakes, too!
Top with pineapple, blueberries, etc.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces lightly with salt and pepper.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add chicken and brown over medium-high heat.
Turn pieces skin side up.
Add wine, 1/4 cup water, carrots, celery, parsley flakes, bouillon granules, thyme and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are fork-tender and chicken near bone is no longer pink.
Transfer meat and vegetables to serving platter. Cover with foil and set aside.

title: colorful cherry dessert
directions: Mix together cherries, sugar, food coloring and flavoring. Dissolve jello in boiling water; add to cherry mixture.
Let congeal until quite firm, but not solid.
Melt marshmallows in scalded milk and cool.
Add to whipped cream.

title: rice-green chiles-cheese bake
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Cook zucchini in small amount of salted water until crisp-tender.
Set aside.

title: salomi
directions: Mix; divide into 3 logs and wrap in foil, shiny side out. Place in fridge for 24 hours.
Puncture logs and place on broiler pan with 2-3 cups of water in bottom of pan.
Bake 300 for 90 minutes.

title: 3 day pickles
directions: Fill a jar with pickles, dill, and 2 cloves.
Add to jar 1/2 c. vinegar, 1/3 c. or less salt, room temperature water.
Drain water into pan, boil water.
Put water back over pickles, cover and refrigerate for three days and enjoy.

title: pork chops in a hurry
directions: Melt butter (don't brown it).
Mix garlic powder, salt and pepper and shake over both sides of chops.
Place on melted butter.
Lay onions on top and then chives.
Keep your temperature the same (not too hot), put lid on it and cook until done, flipping only once.
Takes about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with rice, applesauce and carrots.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased sheet cake pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven I bake mine 45 minutes).

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
