title: betty's macaroni dish
directions: Microwave macaroni for 5 minutes in 1/4 cup oil.
Turn noodles after 2 1/2 minutes.
Chop onion, carrots and celery in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients with water, chopped stewed tomatoes and seasonings.
Bake at 350° in a large casserole dish for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to soft boil over low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to 255°.
Remove from heat and beat in peanut butter by hand.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Bring to a boil the raisins and water; cool.
Cream together the oleo and sugar.
Add flour and soda, alternating with the raisins and juice they were cooked in.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 medium size greased cans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: st. james spinach
directions: Mix the spinach, cottage cheese, nutmeg, eggs, onion and garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Top with the crackers and dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: very special jello salad
directions: Place jello and crumbled cream cheese in bowl and dissolve with boiling water.
Add fresh strawberries with sugar, pineapple (drained), and nuts.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
After jello has thickened, add whipped cream (sweetened) and fold in.
Put back in refrigerator and set.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cover and boil 5 medium potatoes for 20 minutes or until tender with 1/2 medium onion and onion salt.
Blend potatoes and water in blender to a puree.
Take butter, flour and milk in saucepan and heat and stir to thicken.
Add garlic salt and pepper.
Add to potatoes and serve hot.

title: herb rolls
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese, paprika, garlic and sesame seed.
Cut biscuits in half.
Roll in cheese and spice mixture.
Drop in greased 9-inch round cake dish with inverted glass custard cup in center of dish.
Bake in Radarange oven 5 to 5 1/2 minutes on Medium.
Remove custard cup and invert ring on platter.
Serve immediately.
Yields 5 servings.

title: broccoli-yogurt salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add frozen broccoli and stir until broccoli separates and gelatin begins to thicken.
Blend in yogurt; add onion.
Pour mixture into 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Wait 2 hours.
Unmold.
Garnish with salad greens, if desired.

title: no fail thanksgiving turkey
directions: Defrost turkey in refrigerator.
Remove neck and giblets.
Wash turkey in cool water.
Pat dry.
Melt margarine in large pan. Saute chopped liver until no longer pink.
Add onion, celery and parsley and saute until soft.
Add bread cubes and mix.
Add beaten eggs or egg substitute.
Mix well.
Generously sprinkle turkey cavities with salt.
Spoon in stuffing, but do not pack. Brush outside of turkey with melted margarine.
Place in roaster on rack.
Cover with foil tent.
Refer to turkey packaging for proper cooking times.

title: best ever muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Make a hole in center of dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: In large bowl, blend thoroughly the peanut butter and margarine.
Stir in the sugar and Rice Krispies.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture, coating well (use spoon to help, if needed) and place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet until firm.
Store in refrigerator.
Ready to eat after a couple of hours of chilling.

title: sweet sour pork
directions: Cut pork into 1-inch squares.
Mix and knead all of ingredients into meat.
This must be left on meat at least 1/2 hour or longer (overnight).

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat sugar, margarine, corn syrup, salt, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon with hand mixer.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pie shell.
Bake until set, 45 minutes.
Refrigerate any remaining pie.

title: caramel glaze for pound cake
directions: Melt butter over medium heat; stir in brown sugar and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk and continue cooking until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Drizzle over cooked cake and garnish with pecan halves.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in greased pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and roll into balls and press down.

title: steak sizzlers
directions: Put everything in a Ziploc bag and mix. Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Skewer and garnish with favorite vegetables and grill. Can be frozen. Thaw before grilling.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tbsp. cold water.
Add 1 c. boiling water.
Mix crushed pineapple and juice, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Refrigerate to cool.
When it starts to jell, add 2 boxes (or envelopes) of Dream Whip (whipped according to directions on box).
Mix well.
Break cake into pieces 1 to 1 1/2 inches. Alternate in buttered (9 x 13 x 2 inch) baking dish with gelatin mixture.
Cool in refrigerator for a couple of hours.
Frost with 1 box whipped Dream Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spaghetti aglio e olio(spaghetti with garlic and oil)
directions: Put a large pot of water to boil.
In the meantime, put a small saucepan on high heat.
When it is hot, add olive oil; brown garlic lightly.
Add red pepper flakes, herbs and spices (be careful; have lid ready because it will splatter).
Add wine, a few spoons of water and a little salt.
Simmer for a few minutes. When water comes to boil, drop in spaghetti and cook approximately 8 minutes or so (to taste).

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Have lemonade at almost room temperature.
Mix milk and lemonade together.
Add half of Cool Whip.
Make pie crust with graham cracker pie crust.
Put mixture in pie crust; cool.
When pie is cool, spread the rest of the Cool Whip on top when ready to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix in bananas, nuts and dry ingredients sifted together.
Bake in a greased and floured pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve liquid. Mix 6 tablespoons of juice, flour, and sugar together. Cook over low heat until sugar melts. Mix pineapple, cheese, and sugar mixture together. Pour into a greased uncovered 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Sprinkle crushed Ritz over top. Drizzle 1 stick melted butter over crackers. Bake at 350 for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add grease.
Mix thoroughly.
Add enough milk to moisten the dough.
DON'T OVER STIR as the crust will be to hard after it cooks.
The dough will be wet, split dough in two.
Flour board then sprinkle flour on the roll of dough.
Use the pie roller to spread the dough (add flour to your pie roller). Makes a complete pie crust.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Combine all, except candy.
Roll in 1-inch balls and bake in small, ungreased tart pans at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place unwrapped candy in each baked cookie as soon as the cookies come out of oven.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and Crisco oil.
Add Jell-O and mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating continuously.
Stir in strawberries which have been thawed.
Pour into three 9-inch round cake pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; put into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the top and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: turnip green soup
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot; and cook on medium heat for one hour or longer, if desired.
Flavor meld and get better the longer you simmer it.
This looks awful when in the pot, but taste great!
It is a real winter treat served with cornbread!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup, pepper and chopped onions together.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven for 30 minutes.
Put onion rings on the last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: onion topped cornbread
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream and 1/2 cup shredded cheese; set aside.
Combine corn meal, sugar and dill weed.
Stir and set aside.
Combine eggs, milk, corn, oil and hot sauce all at once to corn meal.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Spread onion mix over top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt butter, sugar and dates over low heat, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Stir in all other ingredients. Allow to cool until comfortable to handle.
Form into balls (walnut size) and roll in confectioners sugar.
Now they are ready to eat.

title: pot roast (saucy susan)
directions: In Dutch oven, sear meat until brown on all sides.
Add the Saucy Susan.
Fill empty jar with ketchup and add to pot.
Fill jar again with water and add to pot.
No additional seasoning needed.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 2 to 3 hours.
About 1 hour before meat is done, add potatoes and carrot chunks.

title: ice box fruitcake
directions: Put butter and marshmallows in pot over low heat. Stir until well mixed. In a large dish place graham cracker crumbs; pour marshmallow mixture over graham crackers crumbs; mix well. Add fruits; mix well. Press mixture in a buttered pan; cover cake with waxed paper and refrigerate 48 hours. Remove from pan and wrap in foil until ready to eat. The longer it sets, the better it gets!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and rinse out ketchup bottle with 3/4 c. water and add to mixture. Put
in saucepan and simmer about one hour.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Lay chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1/2 slice of each American and Swiss cheese on top of each chicken breast.
Mix mushroom soup and 7-Up and pour over top.
Mix up Stove Top stuffing according to package directions and spread on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking for an additional 15 minutes.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: To make crust:
Combine brown sugar and flour in a large bowl. Stir in margarine; blend until light and crumbly.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl, blending well; put onto crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and slice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Tear chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix torn bread, soups and can of broth from cooked chicken.
Add 2 well beaten eggs.
Put layer of bread mixture, then layer of chicken.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; 1/2 hour before done, put crumbled corn flakes on top and finish baking.

title: artichoke spinach dip
directions: In medium saucepan over medium-high heat, combine all ingredients. Heat until cheese melts. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: strawberry shortcake surprise
directions: Quarter strawberries; add a little sugar to taste and chill. Cut wedge out of top of cake; save.
Fill cake with sweetened strawberries; replace cake wedge.
Cover cake with Cool Whip; garnish cake with whole strawberries.
Makes 16 servings.

title: mint peas
directions: Cook peas and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook, covered, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove cover and add margarine and creme de menthe.

title: date spread
directions: Blender chop nuts.
Empty in bowl.
Put orange juice concentrate and cream cheese into blender container, cover and process at cream until smooth.
Stop blender, add dates, cover and blender chop; add to nuts and mix well.
Chill.
Yields 1 cup.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs; stir in buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into mixture.
Stir in pecans, cherries and dates.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop with teaspoon 2 inches apart.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes,
only lightly brown.

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Add soups, water and milk. Add 2/3 of noodles.
Pour into greased casserole; cover.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Take off lid and put rest of noodles on top; turn off oven.
Leave in oven a few minutes.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler; cool 10 minute.
Blend cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat in cooled chocolate, blend well.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar, beat until stiff and glossy.
Fold chocolate mixture into beaten egg whites; fold in whipped cream.
Pour into chilled crust, reserving 1/4 of mixture for decorating.
Chill until filling sets slightly.
With tapered spoon, drop reserved mixture in mounds over top of pie.
Chill overnight.

title: homemade chili sauce
directions: Put diced onions in a pot and cover them with water.
Add desired amount of salt and pepper.
Let boil for onions to get done.
After onions are done, add tomato juice.
(Fry ground beef and drain.)
Then add ground beef to the juice.
Let boil until it starts getting a little thick, then add tomato paste and 1 package of chili seasoning mix.
Mix well and add sugar for taste.

title: applesauce cake(diabetics can eat this cake!)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar substitute; combine soda and applesauce and add to first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until just blended.
Pour into nonstick 7 x 11-inch baking pan and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Cut when cool into 15 slices.
Contains 100 calories each!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and cream of chicken soup. Beginning with peas and ending with corn, place ingredients in layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dollop sauce mixture on top layer and smooth to sides of dish.
Top with toasted cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soup, vegetables and chicken in bowl and mix well. Pour into pie shell. Cover with second pie shell and crimp edges. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: festive punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.
Use light or red fruit punch depending on the color punch you desire.
Make ice cubes from limeade or extra fruit punch to avoid diluting punch with regular cubes.
Makes 28 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: annie's bread pudding
directions: Boil milk; add vanilla, sugar, eggs, and butter and pour over bread.
Bake in a well greased casserole dish at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.
Top with caramel sauce and serve.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Boil syrup and sugar about 2 minutes.
Pour slowly over eggs stirring well.
Add butter, vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix pudding and regular milk until it thickens.
Add sweetened condensed milk and frozen whipped topping and mix thoroughly. Alternate layers of wafers, strawberries and pudding mixture in a large bowl.
Repeat until full and top with more whipped topping.

title: hot nacho dip
directions: Pour all ingredients into a slow cooker.
Mix well.
Heat on low for 2 hours.

title: crop soup
directions: Cook all vegetables until done.
Melt butter; add flour.
When smooth, gradually add broth, vegetables, milk and seasonings. Simmer; add cubed cheese.

title: "venison swiss steak"
directions: Steak should be about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Dredge with flour; season with salt and pepper, then brown in table fat or suet. When brown on both sides, add the other ingredients.
Cover tightly and cook in medium oven (350°) or over low flame on top of stove until tender (about 1 1/4 hours).
Remove meat to platter and make a gravy from drippings in the pan.
Serve with baked potatoes and a green salad.
(And, of course, plenty of good black coffee.)

title: chocolate yum yum cake
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine in pan.
Take off fire and mix flour and nuts.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: barbecue sauce-painted spareribs
directions: Simmer all sauce ingredients on low heat until ready to use. Partially cook ribs at 350° about 30 minutes.
Place ribs on barbecue.
Baste with sauce.
Cook and turn.
Baste again until sauce is done and ribs cooked thoroughly.
Sauce can be used for other foods as well.

title: chateaubriand
directions: Place beef on large piece of heavy-duty foil and sprinkle with oregano, garlic salt, flour and pepper.
Roll beef over foil to get the remaining ingredients.
Wrap in foil and place in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Remove 2 hours before cooking.
Add water to the pan and cook 35 minutes at 400°.
This will be medium-rare; cook longer if you prefer your meat medium.
Serve with steamed vegetables.
Serves 8.

title: grillin' out mexican hamburgers
directions: In a large bowl, mix beef with green pepper, onion, chili powder, chili sauce, salt and pepper.
Shape beef into 4 patties, each around an ice cube (grilling melts the ice, leaving the meat juicy).
Grill to desired degree of doneness.
Turn patties often. Toast buns on grill a few minutes before burgers finish cooking. Serves 4.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy; add eggs and jam. Sift dry ingredients together twice. Add to first mixture alternately with the milk. Depending on whether layers are to be thick or thin, prepare 3 or 4 (9 inch) pans. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until done. Stack with Caramel Icing.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine the 2 packages of jello and boiling water.
Let cool. Add pineapple and pie filling.
Let congeal.

title: jello party salad
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan for easy salad removal.

title: potatoes deluxe(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Mix together in large bowl. Pour into casserole (sprayed with Pam), 9 1/2 x 13-inch baking dish (I use a 10 x 14-inch dish). Top with corn flakes or potato chips sauteed in a little butter or 1 small can of onion rings (crushed); do not saute onion rings in butter. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: donna's easy cinnamon butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Slowly add flour.
Add walnuts.
Shape mixture in crescents. Bake 15 minutes.
Cool.
In separate bowl, mix equal parts cinnamon and sugar.
Sprinkle to coat each cookie.
Yields about 36.

title: stone soup
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.

title: easy breakfast strata
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage; drain.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: spicy walnuts
directions: Heat walnut halves at 375° for 5 minutes, stirring once. Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix together flour and sugar. Set aside.
Mix together and bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and Coke.
Pour this mixture over the sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Cook in a greased sheet cake pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then add flour, spice, apples and pecans.
Bake in tube pan for approximately 1 hour.

title: peanut sweet potato pie
directions: Cream
butter,	sugar
and salt until light and fluffy. Combine
sweet
potatoes, eggs and syrup, vanilla and peanuts. Add to butter-sugar mixture and mix until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.	Garnish with two tablespoons chopped peanuts. Bake pie in
preheated
375° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted
in
center comes out clean.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: breakfast egg casserole("like quiche")
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole.
Layer the rest of the ingredients on top of the egg mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Bake casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use casserole dish large enough to contain cut-up chicken in single layer.
Spread rice on bottom of dish.
Pour 2 cups water over rice.
Spread chicken pieces over rice.
Pour undiluted can of mushroom soup over chicken and rice and sprinkle onion soup mix over all.

title: old-fashioned potato soup
directions: In heavy 1-quart saucepan, fry bacon until fat begins to melt. Stir in onion and celery and continue to cook until vegetables are tender but not brown.
Add potato, water, bay leaf, salt, thyme, nutmeg and pepper; bring to a boil and cook, covered, 10 to 15 minutes or until potato is tender.
Fish out bay leaf; mash potato coarsely, leaving plenty of lumps.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a simmer and serve.
Makes two 1 1/2-cup servings.
Modify the amounts to suit your needs.

title: rochelle's casserole
directions: Mix all together, except almonds and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs for top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Make crust of graham crackers and margarine.
Line a Pyrex dish.
Mix Jell-O and water.
Put milk in large bowl; beat until creamy.
Add Jell-O, vanilla and sugar; continue beating.
Add cheese; mix well and put in crust.
Put in refrigerator; let set. Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs or powdered sugar.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine; mix with potatoes.
Add all other ingredients, except corn flakes and margarine.
Mix corn flakes and margarine; top casserole with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Layer in order the first 7 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice and pour over top of other ingredients.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine beaten egg, salt and milk.
Add 1 cup of flour (or enough to make stiff dough).
Roll very thin on floured surface. Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll up loosely.
Slice 1/4-inch wide; unroll.
Spread out and let dry 2 hours.
Drop into boiling soup or boiling, salted water and cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Makes 3 cups cooked noodles.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper.
Drain sausage.
Chop cabbage in pot and add sausage and all other ingredients.
Steam until cabbage is tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, butter, sour cream, baking soda and salt.
Put 1 teaspoon flour with nuts and mix together.
Add nuts and flour; mix well.
Add bananas and mix well.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out dry.
Cool.
tags: baking soda mixed with sour cream

title: persimmon pudding(family favorite; a beth tartan recipe)
directions: Remove the seeds from the persimmons.
Puree.
Mix all ingredients well.
Grease baking dish or pans and pour mixture into baking pans.
Bake at 350° until firm and lightly browned for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, oil and vanilla and mix well.
Add zucchini; mix until thick.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add morsels and nuts.
Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into loaf pan, greased and floured.
Cook at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Allow to cool before cutting into slices.

title: quickie casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Put half the macaroni into a buttered baking dish.
Add all other ingredients, then cover with the remaining macaroni.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown, about 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spice squares
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add molasses, sour milk, spices, baking powder, baking soda, flour, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch and water and place in microwave.
Cook until clear, about 3 minutes on Medium-high.
Cool.
Beat egg whites (room temperature) until foamy.
Gradually add a tablespoon of sugar at a time.
Turn mixer to lower speed and gradually add cornstarch mixture (cooled).
Turn mixer to high speed and beat well.
Spread meringue over cooled pie filling.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In a heavy sauce pan, combine soups, taco sauce and chilies and heat thoroughly.

title: cranberry ripple cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a large bowl; beat butter 30 seconds.
Add sugar and extract; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour mixture and sour cream.
Add to cream mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.
Spread half the batter in a greased and floured tube pan; spoon half cup cranberry sauce over batter.
Spoon remaining batter over sauce.
Top with rest of cranberry sauce. Sprinkle with pecans on top.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: low fat rollups
directions: Mix cream cheese, dried chives, and accent. Lay out each slice of ham and spread mixture on the whole slice. Rollup and slice into thin wheels. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Then serve on town house crackers.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Add butter and 1/3 cup Eagle Brand milk; mix.
Pour 1/2 of mix into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Put rest of milk and caramels in pan and melt.
Pour over cake with pecans and chocolate chips.
Add rest of batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Ice with chocolate icing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Set oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour.

title: "northern italian marinara gravy"
directions: Brown 4 cloves of garlic and chopped onion in oil.
Remove after browning.
Pour tomatoes, parsley flakes, pepper, salt and cheese into hot oil.
Chop the other clove of garlic and stir.

title: lumpia(egg rolls)
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet until brown; drain off fat.
Add chopped onions, cabbage, carrots and about 1 or 2 teaspoons of soy sauce.
Cook together, stir constantly, until vegetables are tender.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Blend water and jello in a blender. Add cream cheese and vanilla; blend until smooth. Stir in 7-Up and pineapple; do not blend.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: summer veggie sauce(low-fat)
directions: Go to Farmer's Market to get freshest possible veggies and select several ripe plum tomatoes and other vegetables.
Wash and chop veggies into sizable chunks.
Place enough olive oil in a large pot or Dutch oven to cover the bottom.
Heat oil (do not allow to smoke) and dump chunky chopped vegetables into pot, tomatoes first.

(If you don't like skins of tomatoes, quickly blanch whole tomatoes in boiling water and peel before chopping.) Cook veggies over medium heat until they soften and liquid forms. Add seasonings and grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve atop angel hair pasta with grated asiago cheese on top.

title: scandinavian meat balls
directions: Mix beef, onion and salt.
Shape into balls.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Remove.
Pour off fat.
Stir 1/2 cup water into pan drippings.
Add 1 cup water to soup mix.
Stir into pan, stirring and bring to a boil.
Cover; heat 10 minutes.
Make egg noodles as directed on package.
When noodles are cooked, drain and top with meat balls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: two toned fudge
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 4 minutes.
Divide in half.
To one half add peanut butter.
Pour onto well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Add chocolate chips to remaining mixture.
Pour on top of peanut butter mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: greens with basil
directions: For salad, place salad greens in a large salad bowl.
Top with apple and mushroom slices.

title: baked hash brown potatoes
directions: Melt half of the margarine.
Mix with thawed hash brown potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sour cream, onion, cream of chicken soup and Cheddar cheese mixture to potatoes.
Melt second half of margarine.
Mix with crushed corn flakes and put on top of potato dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Set butter out for about 6 hours until softened.
Blend butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing well after each one.
Add flour, cream, lemon and vanilla extract.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° until toothpick comes out clean (about 1 hour).

title: persimmon nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, spices, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Add eggs, oil, persimmon pulp and nuts; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 1 hour or 45 minutes if using small pans or until done.

title: fresh cranberry apple casserole
directions: Alternate layers of apples and cranberries in 13 x 9-inch casserole.	Sprinkle each layer with sugar.
Melt margarine and add oats, pecans and brown sugar.
Spread over top layer and bake uncovered for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Set aside.
In bowl of electric mixer, combine shortening, both sugars, grated lemon peel and eggs.
Beat at high speed, frequently guiding mixture into beaters until light and fluffy. Remove beaters.
With spoon, stir in the drained pineapple, then the flour mixture and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake in moderate oven, 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Combine all wet ingredients.
Combine all dry ingredients. Mix together.
Place in greased loaf pan or muffin pans.
Bake at 300° for 70 minutes for loaf pan or 25 to 30 minutes for muffin pan.
Test for doneness by inserting toothpick into center of loaf or muffin.
Toothpick should come out clean.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn before making the syrup.
Combine first three ingredients in 2-quart microwave dish.
Bring to boil (3 minutes on High), then cook on High 2 minutes more.
Stir after each cooking time.
Remove from microwave.
Add baking soda; stir well, then pour over popped corn, which you should have in large grocery bag (brown bag).
Fold down top of bag and shake well.
Cook in bag on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake again; cook 1 1/2 minutes on High.
(May need to add 1 1/2 minutes.)

title: pizza pockets
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Unroll crescent rolls. do not separate into triangles. Take each rectangle piece of dough and roll slightly between 2 pieces of waxed paper. Put a teaspoon or two of pizza sauce in middle of rectangle. Top with pepperoni and cheese. Fold edges over and seal along cracks. Bake for 15 minutes. One tube makes 4 pizza pockets.

title: hamburger pie-excellente!
directions: Brown the ground chuck in skillet.
Drain off all fat! Remove browned meat.
Cook chopped onions in same skillet along with 2 bouillon cubes.
When bouillon cubes are melted and onions are yellow, add 1 can tomato puree and 1 can cut green beans. Sprinkle over with black pepper.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine ingredients together and mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix. Beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Beat whipping cream until stiff. Then fold into pudding mixture.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass bowl.
Top with a layer of wafers and 1 sliced banana.
Repeat layering with mix and wafers and bananas, ending with pudding on top.

title: amigo pita pocket sandwiches
directions: In large skillet, brown turkey; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except pita bread, lettuce and cheese; blend well. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Open pita breads to form pocket.
Line each with lettuce leaves.
Spoon 1/2 cup filling into each pita bread and top with cheese.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve with veggie sticks and fruit.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Let the butter or margarine stand at room temperature until soft, then beat in sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Sift all together.
Roll out mixture and add enough flour to make stiff.
Chill for 1 hour before rolling out.
After chilling, roll thin and cut cookies and put on a cookie or baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 5 to 7 minutes. Yields 50 to 60 cookies.
After baking, you may "paint" the cookies different by using food coloring and tiny paint brushes.

title: quick ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef with onions in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, salt and pepper; mix well. Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Arrange cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: veggie lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water for 8 to 10 minutes. Cook spinach; drain very well.
Cook mushrooms, carrots and onion in oil until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, olives and oregano.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cut cream cheese and beat in with mixer on low or medium speed.
Chill until soft-set. Stir in crushed pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sauerkraut, oil, vinegar, celery, drained garbanzos, sugar, pepper, pimiento, green pepper and onions.
Mix well. Refrigerate at least 12 hours to blend flavors.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: In mixer bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, 3/4 cup milk and Crisco.
Beat vigorously by hand or at medium speed on electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Add the 1/2 cup milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with vanilla frosting.

title: cheddar carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook in small amount of boiling water, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add carrots.
Combine cheese, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Place half of carrots in a 1-quart casserole, then half of cheese cracker mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: norwegian fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Cool; beat until creamy.
Add nut meats.
Pour into buttered pans.

title: banana pineapple dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Beat confectioners sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs for 20 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into the crumbs.
Sprinkle 1/2 banana mixture on top.
Pour remaining layer of sugar mixture and the rest of banana mixture on top.

title: date balls
directions: In a large saucepan, add margarine, sugar, egg and cut up dates.
Cook for 9 minutes over low heat, stirring constantly.
It will thicken.
Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies and nuts.
When cool enough to handle and well mixed, make into small balls, rolling in your hands.
Roll balls into the coconut, which has been heaped on top of waxed paper.
Refrigerate to harden.
Also can store some in freezer as this recipe makes a lot.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate together with flavoring.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add chocolate mixture.
Sift flour and soda.
Mix.
Add milk and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand for 24 hours before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix last 8 ingredients and toss with broccoli and celery. Refrigerate before serving.

title: lite chocolate mousse
directions: In a small saucepan, combine skim milk and gelatin.
Let stand until gelatin is softened.
Stir over low heat about 5 minutes until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat; add cocoa and sugar.
Stir until dissolves.
Stir in 1 cup evaporated skim milk and vanilla.
Refrigerate about 2 hours or until mixture is syrup-like.

title: pizza dough
directions: Add lard to scalded milk and cool to lukewarm.
Add crumbled yeast and let soften for about 10 minutes.
Add flour and salt and mix thoroughly.
Knead dough for about 5 minutes.
Place on greased cookie sheet or round pizza pan.
Cover with towel and let stand in warm place until doubled in size.
Add Pizza Topping as desired after punching down dough and patting 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grandma's big whites
directions: Beat eggs to a froth.
Mix shortenings together and cream. Add sugar, eggs, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix together until creamy.
In a separate bowl, mix the sour cream, baking soda and baking powder; beat fast until bubbly.
Combine both mixtures and mix together.
Add flour.
(Dough will be sticky.)
Roll out onto a floured board.
Roll to desired thickness.
Cut out.
Bake at 425°.

title: cal-o-rific dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve with Wheat Thins crackers.
Makes 1 cup dip.

title: spinach pie
directions: Saute onions in olive oil in frying pan until tender (I use water to cut down on fat).
In a large bowl, combine spinach, parsley, dill, eggs and cheese.
Add scallions, mix well.

Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased (or Pam) baking pan with 4 sheets phyllo dough, brushing each sheet with butter or margarine. Spread spinach mixture over top of dough and top with 3 sheets of dough, brushing each with butter.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off grease.
In a large pot, add mixed vegetables and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add ground beef; cook for about 30 minutes on low heat.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chiffon pie
directions: Blend and press into 10-inch pie plate.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil, rinse and drain spaghetti.
Add bell pepper (chopped fine), onion (chopped fine) and all other ingredients.
Mix together and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: dee's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs one at a time.
Mix well after each egg.
Add flavoring.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk; fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes in 325° oven.
Pour syrup (recipe follows) over cake in pan when removed from oven.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; add eggs and blend.
Dissolve soda in 1 tablespoon hot water.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend all ingredients well, adding nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
You may also use sweetened chocolate chopped up if you don't have chocolate chips.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans well (use juice), beat eggs and add sugar and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.
Freezes well.
Tastes like pecan pie.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat iron skillet over stove with butter in it.
Mix together all other ingredients and add 2 tablespoons of melted butter to mixture.
Place mixture in heated skillet.
Place in oven at 450° until golden brown, approximately 25 minutes.

title: pretzel salad(a jay fox favorite)
directions: First Layer:
Crush pretzels fine.
Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press into Pyrex dish.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Prepare bottom crust by mixing together flour, butter and pecans until crumb like.
Press mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Shell shrimp.
Cook onion, celery and garlic in salad oil until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt, sugar, chili powder and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon water; stir into sauce.
Cook, stirring until bubbly. Add peeled shrimp and green pepper.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Pour 1/2 in pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels, milk and butter on low heat (or use ice cream topping instead of the caramels, milk and butter).
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle pecans and chips on top.
Put rest of cake mix on.
Bake 20 more minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms.
Cut cheese into bite size chunks and put on bottom of crust.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Beat eggs and cream together and pour them on top of mushrooms and onion. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then turn oven down to 350°; bake another 20 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add 2 egg yolks.
Fold in pineapple, pecans and egg whites.
Make sandwich with 3 vanilla wafers and fill with filling.
Freeze.
Roll in Cool Whip and coconut.

title: creole shrimp jambalaya
directions: Chop onion and brown lightly in margarine.
Add flour, thyme, bay leaf, parsley and garlic salt.
Let brown very slowly for about 5 minutes.
Add chili pepper, finely chopped tomatoes and broth.
Let boil; add shrimp.
Let cook 5 minutes.
Add rice and season to taste.
Cover and let cook about 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and small stems.
Add raisins, sunflower seeds and onion; toss and add dressing.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over salad and mix well.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onion and spices in skillet.
In large saucepan, put tomatoes (break large pieces with fork) and tomato paste.
Add meat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer meat, noodles and cheeses.
If using cottage cheese, layer on top of meat before noodles.
Continue layering, ending with noodles.
Sprinkle top with any cheese leftover.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in about 3/4 cup water for about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients in large mixing bowl and pour broccoli and onion over them and mix together.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until firm.
Use a large enough casserole dish to allow some bubbling while cooking.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish.
Top with bacon slices or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cholesterol free popovers
directions: Beat egg whites at medium speed until frothy.
Beat in milk and margarine until blended.
Beat in flour and salt until smooth. Fill 12 greased muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes until nicely browned at 375°.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Melt cheese in crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix.
Keep warm on low setting.
Serve with nacho or tortilla chips.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix all together and pour into ice cream churn and freeze.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix in a separate bowl.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl, add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip, stir in 1 cup of the cookies and the rocks into the pudding mix.
Put in pie crust, sprinkle rest of cookies on top.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.

title: party punch slush
directions: Mix together the water and sugar; boil 3 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix together and freeze (large plastic bags or plastic freezer container).

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Sprinkle liberally with paprika.
Mix all together and marinate shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for large shrimp or 20 minutes for small shrimp, basting often.
